obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37224)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37224&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Ajmer Tenancy and`
  line `Land Records Act, 1950.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the State of Ajmer.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once, except Part III of Chapter XII which shall come into force on such`
  line `date as the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37225)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37225&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ajmer-Merwara Agrarian Relief (Second) Ordinance, 1949 (30 of 1949), is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) When this Act or any portion thereof comes into force in Ajmer, so much of any Act, Regulation`
  line `or notification in force therein, or any condition of a jagir or istimrari sanad, as is inconsistent with this`
  line `Act or with such portion, shall be deemed to have been repealed or superseded by this Act or by such`
  line `portion, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37226)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37226&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Any rule, notification, proclamation and order issued, authority and power conferred,`
  line `lease granted, right acquired, liability incurred, rent fixed, and any other thing done under any Act,`
  line `Ordinance, Regulation or notification, or under any jagir or istimrar sanad, as the case may be, shall, in`
  line `so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been respectively issued,`
  line `conferred, granted, acquired, incurred, fixed and done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37227)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37227&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,`
  line
  line `(1) all words and expressions used to denote the possessor of any right title or interest, whether the`
  line `same be proprietary or otherwise, shall be deemed to include the predecessors and successors in right, title`
  line `or interest of such person;`
  line
  line `(2) "agricultural year" means the year commencing on the first day of June and ending on the`
  line `thirty-first day of May next following;`
  line
  line `(3) "agriculturist" means a person who earns his livelihood wholly or principally--`
  line
  line `(a) by the cultivation of land personally, or through servants or by hired labour, or`
  line
  line `(b) as artisan or field-labourer, paid in cash or kind for work connected with agriculture, and`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(i) a landlord whose interest in the stable land of the village does not exceed 120 acres, and`
  line
  line `(ii) a tenant who sub-lets his land in accordance with the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An agriculturist who, without any intention of changing his profession as such,`
  line `temporarily ceases to so earn his livelihood, or who if prevented from so earning his livelihood by age or`
  line `bodily infirmity, or by absence due to service in the military, naval or air forces of India, or by`
  line `confinement in prison, does not thereby cease to be an agriculturist;`
  line
  line `(4) "assistant commissioner" includes an additional assistant commissioner and an extra assistant`
  line commissioner;
  line
  line `(5) "batai" means division of the produce on the threshing-floor;`
  line
  line `(6) "bighori" means money rent per bigha of land;`
  line
  line `(7) "biswadar" means--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who is recorded as plot-proprietor in the settlement khewat of 1874 and is`
  line `continuously so recorded since, or who, but for an error or omission, would have been so`
  line `continuously recorded; or`
  line
  line `(b) any member of the proprietary body who becomes an owner of land under section 7 of the`
  line `Ajmer Land and Revenue Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877), or`
  line
  line `(c) any person who becomes, or is declared, a biswadar under the provisions of this Act, and`
  line `includes a person admitted to the occupation of land under a lease guaranteeing hereditary rights of`
  line `ownership and enjoyment on condition of his permanently developing such land by sinking a well or`
  line `otherwise, and who accordingly developed such land and was, before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `recorded as plot proprietor thereof in the khewat;`
  line
  line `(8) "cess" means a cess declared payable under sub-section (2) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(9) "collector" means the collector of Ajmer or any other office appointed by the Chief Commissioner`
  line `to discharge the functions of a collector under this Act, and includes an additional collector;`
  line
  line `(10) "confirming court" means a court to which the record of a case it submitted in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act for confirmation of any decree or order passed therein;`
  line
  line `(11) "decree" means an order which is drawn up in the form of a decree as prescribed;`
  line
  line `(12) "holding" means a parcel or parcels of land held under one lease, engagement or grant or, in the`
  line `absence of such lease, engagement or grant, under one tenure, and in section 26 includes a well on a`
  line holding;
  line
  line `(13) "improvement" means, with reference to a tenant's holding,--`
  line
  line `(i) a dwelling house erected on the holding by the tenant for his own occupation, or a cattle-shed,`
  line `or a store-house or any other construction for agricultural purposes, erected or set up by him on his`
  line `holding, and`
  line
  line `(ii) any work which adds materially to the value of the holding and is consistent with the purpose`
  line `for which it was let, and which, if not executed on the holding, is either executed directly for its`
  line `benefit or is, after execution, made directly beneficial to it, and, subject to the foregoing provisions of`
  line `this clause, includes-`
  line
  line `(a) the construction of a well, water channel, and other work for the supply or distribution of`
  line `water for agricultural purposes,`
  line
  line `(b) the construction of any work for the drainage of land, or for the protection of land from`
  line `floods, or from erosion or other damage by water,`
  line
  line `(c) the reclaiming, clearing, enclosing, levelling, or terracing of land,`
  line
  line `(d) the erection in the immediate vicinity of the holding, otherwise than on the village site, of`
  line `a building required for the convenient or profitable use or occupation of the holding,`
  line
  line `(e) the construction of a tank or other work for the storage of water for agricultural`
  line `purposes, and`
  line
  line `(f) the renewal or reconstruction of any of the foregoing works, or such alterations therein, or`
  line `additions thereto, as are not of the nature of mere repairs:`
  line
  line `Provided that such clearance, water channel, levelling, embankment, enclosure, temporary`
  line `well or other work as is made in the ordinary course of cultivation and without incurring any`
  line `special expenditure shall not be deemed to be an improvement;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A work which benefits several holdings may be deemed to be an improvement`
  line `with respect to each of such holdings;`
  line
  line `(14) "istimrari estate" means an estate in respect of which an istimrari sanad has been granted`
  line `by the Chief Commissioner before the commencement of the Ajmere Land and Revenue`
  line `Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877); and`
  line
  line `"istimrardar" means the person to whom such sanad has been granted, or any other person who`
  line `becomes entitled to the istimrari estate in succession to him in accordance with the provisions of the said`
  line Regulation;
  line
  line `(15) "jagirdar" means a person to whom the revenue of any land has been assigned under a sanad`
  line `issued by the Chief Commissioner before the commencement of the Ajmere Land and Revenue`
  line `Regulation, 1877;`
  line
  line `(16) "khudkasht" means land cultivated by a proprietor as such, either himself, or by servants or by`
  line `hired labour;`
  line
  line `(17) "kuta" means an estimate or appraisement of the standing crop;`
  line
  line `(18) "lag" means--`
  line
  line `(a) a levy in cash imposed on a tenant`
  line
  line `(i) on the occasion of a ceremony in the family of the landlord or the tenant, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by way of tax on a well or plough or as fee for settlement of rent accounts; or--`
  line
  line `(b) any other levy in cash over and above the rent payable by a tenant, but does not include a fee`
  line `specified in the First Schedule or an assessment leviable, or a local rate payable under any law for the`
  line `time being in force in the State;`
  line
  line `(19) "land" means land which is let or held for the raising of crops or garden produce, or for purposes`
  line `subservient thereto, and includes land covered by water used for the purpose of growing singhara or other`
  line `producer but does not include land for the time being occupied by a building or appurtenant thereto, other`
  line `than a building which is an improvement;`
  line
  line `(20) "landholder" means the person to whom rent is, or, but for a contract, express or implied, would`
  line `be, payable, and includes shamlat committee created or recognised under the provisions of section 180;`
  line
  line `(21) "landlord" means the proprietor of a village, or of a share or specified plot therein, and`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(i) in case of land in respect of which an istimrari sanad has been granted, any person by whom`
  line `an estate, a village, or a portion of an estate or village is held, whether under a separate engagement to`
  line `pay revenue or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) a jagirdar; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a trustee, a manager, a superintendent, a mutawalli, or a body of persons appointed to`
  line `administer a religious endowment, a trust, or waqf property, or the shamlat deh land of a village;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In clauses (20) and (21), the word "landholder" or "landlord" shall include--`
  line
  line `(i) a mortgagee with possession,`
  line
  line `(ii) a lessee of proprietary right, and`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of property of which superintendence has been assumed by the Court of Wards under`
  line `section 6 of the Ajmere Government Wards Regulation, 1888 (1 of 1888) or which has been attached`
  line `under section 82 of the Ajmere Land and Revenue Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877), the collector;`
  line
  line `(22) "lease" includes the counterpart of a lease;`
  line
  line `(23) "legal practitioner" means any person who is, for the time being enrolled as an advocate or`
  line `pleader by the Judicial Commissioner of Ajmer;`
  line
  line `(24) "minor" means a person who, under section 3 of the Indian Majority Act, 1875 (9 of 1875), has`
  line `not attained majority;`
  line
  line `(25) "muafi" means a definite portion of land held revenue-free under a sanad issued by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, and a "muafidar" means the holder of such muafi;`
  line
  line `(26) "neg" means--`
  line
  line `(a) a levy in kind imposed on a tenant as--`
  line
  line `(i) seri, sawai-batti or any other kind of levy made on the division of the produce of a`
  line `holding, or`
  line
  line `(ii) kasas (dishes) of food or sweetmeats given on the occasion of marriage or any other`
  line `ceremony or the money equivalent thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other levy in kind over and above the rent payable by a tenant;`
  line
  line `(27) "order" means the formal expression of a decision of any authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(28) "parabund-barani" means enclosed low lying land, the cultivation of which depends on the`
  line `rainfall and the silt deposited thereon by the inflow of water from the catchment area;`
  line
  line `(29) "pay", "payable" and "payment", when used with reference to rent, include "deliver",`
  line `"deliverable" and "delivery";`
  line
  line `(30) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(31) "produce of a holding" means a crop or any other produce of the land standing on the holding, or`
  line `which has been grown on the holding and has been reaped or gathered, and is deposited on the holding or`
  line `on a threshing floor;`
  line
  line `(32) "State" means the State of Ajmer;`
  line
  line `(33) "rent" means whatever is paid or payable in money or kind, or partly in money and partly in`
  line `kind, by a tenant on account of the use or occupation of land held by him;`
  line
  line `(34) "registered" means registered under any law for the time being in force for the registration of`
  line documents;
  line
  line `(35) "revenue court" means all or any of the following authorities when acting under this Act or any`
  line `rule made thereunder, namely,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Commissioner,`
  line
  line `(ii) the collector,`
  line
  line `(iii) a record officer, an assistant record officer and a rent-rate officer,`
  line
  line `(iv) a sub-divisional officer,`
  line
  line `(v) an assistant commissioner,`
  line
  line `(vi) a tahsildar,`
  line
  line `(vii) a naib-tahsildar empowered by the collector under clause (b) of section 178, and`
  line
  line `(viii) a person or a body of persons invested with powers to hear and dispose of cases under`
  line `clause (a) or (b) of section 180;`
  line
  line `(36) "revenue" means land revenue;`
  line
  line `(37) "sayar" means whatever is payable by a lessee or licensee on account of the right of gathering`
  line `produce, forest rights, fisheries or the use of water for irrigation from artificial sources; and includes a fee`
  line `specified in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(38) "stable land" means land which, because of facilities of irrigation, quality of the soil or other`
  line `advantages, is capable of being regularly cultivated, and is demarcated as stable land by the rent-rate`
  line `officer, or any other authority, appointed for the purpose, and, subject to the foregoing provisions,`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(i) land in the bed of a tank or nadi which dries up in time for the rabi sowing, and`
  line
  line `(ii) mal, gormia or parabund-barani:`
  line
  line `Provided that, until such time as demarcation is made, the provisions regarding demarcation shall`
  line `not be deemed to be a part of this clause;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A land which is capable of being regularly cultivated shall not cease to be so regarded`
  line `if, in any year, it has been left fallow, or could not be cultivated on account of failure of rainfall or for any`
  line `other reason;`
  line
  line `(39) "sub-tenant" means a person who holds land from the tenant thereof, or from a rent-free grantee,`
  line `or from a grantee at a favourable rate of rent, and by whom rent is, or, but for a contract express or`
  line `implied, would be, payable;`
  line
  line `(40) "tenant" means a person who holds land of another person and is, or, but for a contract express or`
  line `implied, would be, liable to pay rent for such land to such other person and, except when a contrary`
  line `intention appears, includes a sub-tenant, but does not include--`
  line
  line `(a) a person to whom a tenancy holding is transferred otherwise than under the provisions of this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `(b) except as otherwise provided, a rent-free grantee, a grantee at a favourable rate of rent or a`
  line `holder of village service grant, and`
  line
  line `(c) a person to whom only the right to cut grass or to graze cattle is granted, whether with or`
  line `without consideration; and`
  line
  line `(41) "year of settlement" means, with reference to any area of the State, any year or period between`
  line `November 1940 and June 1947 during which the record or settlement operations were in force in such`
  line area.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37228)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of landlord and tenant to act through agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37228&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Anything which is by this Act required or`
  line `permitted to be done by a landlord or a tenant may be done by his authorised agent, and, in the absence of`
  line `evidence of a contrary intention, in dealings between a landlord and a tenant such agent shall be deemed`
  line `to be acting under the authority of his principal:`
  line
  line `Provided that, except as provided in section 198, a legal practitioner or his clerk or employee, or a`
  line `petition-writer shall not act as authorised agent of such landlord or tenant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "authorised agent" includes a kamdar of a jagirdar or istimrardar.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37229)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Primary rights of tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37229&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A tenant, other than a sub-tenant, shall have a right--`
  line
  line `(i) subject, in the case of clause (a), or (b), to the provisions of the First Schedule and to the`
  line `payment of fee, if any, specified therein--`
  line
  line `(a) to possess, in the village in which his holding is situated, a site on which he may build one`
  line `residential house for himself and his family and, when necessary, to repair and rebuild it, to sell`
  line `the materials of such house and, with the written consent of the landlord, to transfer the right of`
  line `residence therein to any tenant of such village;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause 'residential house' shall include a cattleshed, and a store-house`
  line `for stocking fodder, manure and agricultural implements.`
  line
  line `(b) to use the waste-land of the village for grazing and, pasturing his cattle and other domestic`
  line `animals and for threshing corn;`
  line
  line `(ii) when rent is paid by batai or bighori, to allow only prescribed weights and measures to be`
  line `used for determining such rent; and`
  line
  line `(iii) where in any area bighori is charged at customary rate, to grow cotton at such rate on not`
  line `more than one-fourth of the irrigable area of his holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37230)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Prohibition of certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37230&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant shall not be--`
  line
  line `(i) ejected from his holding otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) evicted from his residential house, other than a house which is an improvement, merely`
  line `because he has surrendered, or has been ejected from his holding in the village; or`
  line
  line `(iii) compelled to render any service, or to allow the use of his cattle or agricultural implements,`
  line `to his landholder, with or without remuneration.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section and of sections 6 and 62 shall, so far as they are applicable, apply to`
  line `a rent-free grantee, a grantee at a favourable rate of rent, a holder of village service grant, and an artisan`
  line `or a village-workman paid in cash or kind, for work connected with agriculture as they apply to a`
  line `hereditary tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37231)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Prohibition against deprivation of certain rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37231&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding any custom or contract`
  line `to the contrary, every lease or agreement between a land-holder and a tenant, whether made before or`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, which purports, or would operate, to prohibit or restrict a tenant from`
  line `acquiring, exercising or enforcing any right conferred on, or secured to, him by this Act, shall be void to`
  line `the extent of such prohibition or restriction.`
  line
  line `(2) When land, not previously cultivated, has been reclaimed by, or at the expense of, the landholder`
  line `and let to a tenant, or has been let to a tenant in order that it should be reclaimed by him or at his expense,`
  line `then for a period of twelve years after such land was let, nothing in sub-section (1) shall be construed as`
  line `affecting any condition of a contract which relates to payment of rent or to enhancement, abatement or`
  line `variation of rent of such land, or which provides that, during any period for which such land is to be held`
  line `free of rent or on favourable terms, the tenant is liable to ejectment for breach of any such condition.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--When land has remained uncultivated for a period of five years, it shall, for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (2), be deemed to be land not previously cultivated.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37232)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Certain rights of landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37232&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Subject, in case of clause (iii), to the conditions of an istimrari`
  line `sanad and to the provisions of any law for the time being in force, a landlord shall have a right--`
  line
  line `(i) where in any area bighori is charged at customary rate and cotton is grown on more than`
  line `one-fourth of the irrigable area of the holding of a tenant, to charge rent on the land in excess of the`
  line `one-fourth area on which cotton is grown at a rate specified in the second proviso to section 64;`
  line
  line `(ii) at all reasonable times, to enter, or depute his servant, agent or surveyor to enter, upon any`
  line `land comprised in his estate for the purpose of surveying and measuring such land or for any other`
  line `lawful purpose; and`
  line
  line `(iii) if he has a proprietary interest in an istimrari estate, to open of work a mine or grant a lease`
  line `for the purpose, or to undertake, or to issue a licence to any other person to undertake, prospecting`
  line `work for discovering new sources of supply of minerals.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37233)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Definition.
  content `Niji jot means khudkasht demarcated under the provision of this Chapter.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37233&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37234)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Application for demarcation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37234&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, at the commencement of this Act, the proprietor of a`
  line `village or a part thereof or a specific area therein, was cultivating any land as khudkasht, he may, within`
  line `six months of such commencement, apply to the sub-divisional officer for demarcation of such khudkasht`
  line `a niji jot.`
  line
  line `(2) With his application, the applicant shall file a list, giving the area and survey number or other`
  line `description of the khudkasht to be so demarcated and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37235)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Order of demarcation of niji jot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37235&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the receipt of such application the sub-divisional`
  line `officer shall issue a proclamation calling upon all persons who claim an interest in such land to file`
  line `objections, if any, within the period specified in such proclamation.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after hearing the objections, if any, and making such further inquiry as he deems fit, the`
  line `sub-divisional officer is satisfied that the land to be demarcated as niji jot has been held by the applicant`
  line `as his khudkasht since the agricultural year beginning on the first day of June, 1948, he shall pass an order`
  line `for the demarcation of such land as niji jot and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order`
  line `passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37236)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Demarcation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37236&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The sub-divisional officer shall have the demarcation made on the spot and shall`
  line `prepare and place on record a map, indicating the plots demarcated as niji jot.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37237)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Status of tenant of niji jot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37237&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `A landlord may let his niji jot subject to the same restrictions as`
  line `apply to sub-letting by a hereditary tenant under section 27:`
  line
  line `Provided that if such landlord lets his land which is niji jot in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `section, such land shall cease to be niji jot and the person to whom the land is so let shall become`
  line `hereditary tenant thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37238)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Succession to niji jot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37238&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `On the death of the holder of niji jot, the niji jot rights shall devolve in`
  line `accordance with the law which regulates the succession of proprietary right in such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37239)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Collector's powers to let to tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37239&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the collector is satisfied that the landlord of an estate or`
  line `village, without good reason, keeps large areas of his niji jot and other culturable land uncultivated, or`
  line `that an emergency has arisen for bringing under cultivation land which has not been previously cultivated`
  line `or, if previously cultivated, has remained uncultivated for more than three years, he may,`
  line
  line `(i) with the previous sanction of the Chief Commissioner, take possession of such land, and`
  line
  line `(ii) notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, allot it for cultivation on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be prescribed, and`
  line
  line `the person to whom the land is so allotted shall, unless he is the landlord at such land, be deemed to have`
  line `been admitted as tenant within the meaning of clause (b) of section 22:`
  line
  line `Provided that, while giving his sanction under clause (i), the Chief Commissioner may exempt from`
  line `its operation any land which is used as pasture land or threshing-floor, or for some other purpose for the`
  line `benefit of the public.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37240)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Classes of tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37240&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `There shall be, for the purposes of this Act, the following clauses of tenants,`
  line namely,--
  line
  line `(a) occupancy tenants;`
  line
  line `(b) exproprietary tenants;`
  line
  line `(c) hereditary tenants; and`
  line
  line `(d) non-occupancy tenants.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37241)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Occupancy tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37241&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every person--`
  line
  line `(a) other than a person to whom the provisions of section 7 of the Ajmere Land and Revenue`
  line `Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877) apply, who, before the commencement of this Act, was admitted to the`
  line `occupation of land and who has, before such commencement, sunk a well, reclaimed or otherwise`
  line `developed such land, or`
  line
  line `(b) who was recorded in the year of settlement as tenant with a permanent right of tenancy`
  line `(mazara-i-mustaqil) and has continued in possession since,`
  line
  line `shall be called an occupancy tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37242)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Exproprietary tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37242&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, at the commencement of this Act, an exproprietary tenant in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Ajmere Land and Revenue Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877), or`
  line
  line `(b) acquires exproprietary rights in accordance with the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be called an exproprietary tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37243)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Acquisition of exproprietary rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37243&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the whole of the interest of a sole proprietor of a`
  line `village or of a specific area thereof is transferred, either by foreclosure or sale in execution of a decree or`
  line `order of a civil or revenue court, or by voluntary alienation, otherwise than (a) by gift or (b) by exchange`
  line `of specific areas between co-sharers of the village, he shall become an exproprietary tenant of the whole`
  line `of his khudkasht in such village or area which he has cultivated continuously for three years or more at`
  line `the date of such transfer, and shall be entitled to hold the same at a rate payable by an exproprietary tenant`
  line `under sections 63 and 64.`
  line
  line `(2) If a part only of the interest of a sole proprietor of a village or of a specific area thereof is so`
  line `transferred, or where there are two or more co-sharers in the proprietary interest of a village or of specific`
  line `area thereof, and such transfer relates to the whole or part of the proprietary interest of some of them,`
  line `exproprietary rights shall accrue in so much of khudkasht so cultivated as appertains or corresponds to the`
  line `part of the interest so transferred and, unless by mutual agreement the transferor and the transferee have`
  line `demarcated the area in which exproprietary rights have accrued, and fixed the rent, not higher than the`
  line `rent specified in sections 63 and 64, the sub-divisional officer shall, in the course of mutation proceedings`
  line `or, if more convenient, in a separate proceeding, started on his own motion, or on the application of the`
  line `exproprietary tenant or the landlord, or on the report of the patwari, demarcate such area and declare the`
  line `rent in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) A mortgage shall be deemed to be a voluntary alienation within the meaning of sub-section (1), if`
  line `it has the effect of transferring proprietary possession of the land mortgaged from the mortgagor to the`
  line `mortgagee but not otherwise.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), (2) or (3), exproprietary rights shall not accrue in`
  line `grove-land, or in land transferred for any purpose inconsistent with the existence of a right of cultivation`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(5) After disposing of the case for demarcation of the exproprietary area and declaration of rent`
  line `thereon under sub-section (2), the sub-divisional officer shall submit the record of the case for`
  line `confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37244)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Relinquishment of exproprietary rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37244&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), an`
  line `agreement for the relinquishment of exproprietary rights shall be void, whether such agreement was`
  line `entered into before or after such rights accrued.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the first proviso to section 57, where the land transferred`
  line `by mortgage of the kind specified in sub-section (3) of section 20 consists wholly of a specific area of`
  line `khudkasht of three or more years, the mortgagor may, by simultaneous agreement in writing, waive his`
  line `exproprietary rights, and in that case the mortgaged land shall, if the mortgagor redeems the mortgage`
  line `within ten years of the date of the transfer, be restored to him unencumbered with any tenancy rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (37245)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Hereditary tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37245&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 23, every person who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, at the commencement of this Act, a tenant of land, not being an exproprietary tenant, an`
  line `occupancy tenant or a sub-tenant, or`
  line
  line `(b) is, after the commencement of this Act, admitted as a tenant otherwise than as a sub-tenant, or`
  line `otherwise than as a tenant to whom niji jot is let in accordance with the provisions of section 14, or`
  line
  line `(c) under the provisions of this Act, acquires hereditary rights, shall be called a hereditary tenant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the word "sub-tenant" shall not include a person who`
  line `holds land from a relation, dependant or servant of the landholder or, in an estate mentioned in the Second`
  line `Schedule, from a transferee of an interest in a holding or part thereof, whether the transfer was made`
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act, unless such relation, dependant, servant or transferee`
  line `proves to the satisfaction of the court that he is a genuine tenant of such land or such holding or part`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (37246)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Land in which hereditary rights shall not accrue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37246&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in this Act,`
  line `hereditary rights shall not accrue in--`
  line
  line `(i) unstable land, or`
  line
  line `(ii) grove-land, pasture-land, bir, or land, covered by water, used for the purpose of growing`
  line `singhara or other produce, or`
  line
  line `(iii) land used for casual or occasional cultivation in the bed of a river or a stream, or`
  line
  line `(iv) land acquired or held for a public purpose or for a work of public utility, or`
  line
  line `(v) the khudkasht of a landlord who is serving in the military, naval or air forces of India, so long`
  line `as he remains in such service and for two years after the cessation of such service:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there are several co-sharers in such khudkasht and not all of them are in such`
  line `service, the provisions of this clause shall apply only when the co-sharers who are not in such service`
  line `belong to one or more of the following classes, namely, females, minors, lunatics, idiots or persons`
  line `incapable of cultivating by reason of blindness or physical infirmity, or confinement in prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (37247)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Non-occupancy tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37247&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All tenants other than occupancy tenants, exproprietary tenants and`
  line `hereditary tenants shall be non-occupancy tenants.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (37248)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Interest of a tenant, if heritable and transferable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37248&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The interest of an occupancy tenant, an`
  line `exproprietary tenant, a hereditary tenant find a non-occupancy tenant is heritable, but is not transferable,`
  line `otherwise than by sublease as hereinafter provided, or by transfer or surrender to a co-tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (37249)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Prohibition against certain kind of transfer or sub-lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37249&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No tenant shall sub-let, or`
  line `otherwise transfer, the whole or any portion of his holding in consideration of a debt, whether reserving or`
  line `not reserving rent to be paid periodically.`
  line
  line `(2) No sub-tenant shall sub-let the whole or any portion of his holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (37250)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Right to sub-let.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37250&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 26 and sub-sections (2) to (4) of this`
  line `section, a tenant may sub-let the whole or any portion of his holding.`
  line
  line `(2) No occupancy, exproprietary or hereditary tenant shall sub-let the whole or any portion of his`
  line holding--
  line
  line `(a) to a person other than an agriculturist, or`
  line
  line `(b) for a term exceeding three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that a period of not less than three years shall intervene between the expiry of one sublease and the beginning of the next sub-lease.`
  line
  line `(3) No non-occupancy tenant, other than a sub-tenant, shall sub-let the whole or any portion of his`
  line `holding for a term exceeding one year.`
  line
  line `(4) The rent payable by a sub-tenant to an occupancy, an exproprietary, a hereditary or a`
  line `non-occupancy tenant shall be an amount not exceeding one and one-fifth of rent payable by such tenant`
  line `to his land-holder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the restrictions imposed by clause (b) of sub-section (2) on sub-letting of a holding or`
  line `portion thereof shall not apply when the lessor is a female, a minor, a lunatic, an idiot, or a person`
  line `incpabale of cultivating by reason of blindness, or any physical infirmity, or service in the military, naval`
  line `or air forces of India, or confinement in prison:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in the case of a holding held jointly by more persona than one, the provisions of`
  line `the first proviso shall not apply unless all such persons belong to one or more of the categories specified`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (37251)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Tenancy, when extinguished.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37251&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The interest of a tenant in his holding or part thereof, as the case`
  line `may be, shall be extinguished--`
  line
  line `(a) when he dies, leaving no heir entitled to inherit; or`
  line
  line `(b) when his ejectment is ordered; or`
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provisions of sections 57 and 58, when he surrenders or abandons the`
  line `holding; or`
  line
  line `(d) when his land is acquired under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894); or`
  line
  line `(e) when he is deprived of possession of his holding otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and has not applied for recovery of possession within the period of limitation`
  line `specified in section 102 or 104, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(f) when the mortgage referred to in section 21 has been redeemed by the mortgagor as provided`
  line `in that section; or`
  line
  line `(g) when he acquires, or succeeds to, the entire proprietary right in his holding, or where the`
  line `holder of the entire proprietary right over a holding inherits or otherwise acquires the tenancy rights`
  line `in such holding:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of ejectment which is submitted for confirmation under the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall extinguish the tenancy, until such order has become final.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (37252)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Life tenancy of female, when extinguished.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37252&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 28,`
  line `the surrender of her holding by a female tenant with life interest shall not extinguish her tenancy, unless`
  line `such surrender is made with the written consent of nearest reversioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (37253)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Rights of sub-tenant on extinction of tenant's interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37253&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subjects to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2), the extinction of the interest of a tenant shall operate to extinguish the interest of any`
  line `sub-tenant holding under him.`
  line
  line `(2) When the right of a tenant in any land is extinguished under the provisions of clause (g) of`
  line `section 28 the sub-tenant, if any, of such land shall become a hereditary tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (37254)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Vacating of holding on extinction of right.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37254&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Except as otherwise provided in this Act, when the`
  line `interest of a tenant or sub-tenant is extinguished he shall vacate his holding, but shall have, in respect of`
  line `the removal of any crop the same rights as a tenant would have upon ejectment in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (37255)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Possession of land not vacated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37255&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a sub-tenant, to whom the provisions of section 31 apply,`
  line `does not vacate the holding, the person entitled to possession of such holding shall, on application to the`
  line `tahsildar be put in possession thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The tahsildar shall, after deciding the dispute, if any, arising between the parties, submit the`
  line `record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (37256)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Division of holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37256&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A division of a holding shall be effected--`
  line
  line `(a) by agreement between the co-tenants; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the order of the tahsildar, passed on an application under this section by a co-tenant against`
  line `the others and the landholder:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such agreement shall be binding on the landholder, unless he agrees thereto in`
  line `writing:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such application shall be entertained if, as a results of division, the area of the`
  line `share of a co-tenant is reduced to less than ten acres.`
  line
  line `(2) If the holding to be divided is assessed to fixed money rent, the division shall be accompanied by`
  line `the distribution of rent payable in respect of each portion of the holding so divided.`
  line
  line `(3) After deciding the case, the tahsildar shall submit the record of the case for confirmation of the`
  line `order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (37257)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Co-tenant's right to claim division of produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37257&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of a holding to which the second`
  line `proviso to sub-section (1) of section 33 applies, the tahsildar may, on the application of a co-tenant,`
  line `specify the share of such co-tenant in the produce of such holding and depute an officer to divide the`
  line `produce in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (3) of section 77 which shall, mutatis`
  line `mutandis, apply to such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(2) The order of the tahsildar under sub-section (2) shall not affect the right of a co-tenant to obtain a`
  line `declaration in respect of his share in such holding under clause (ii) of sub-section (1) of section 43.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (37258)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Right of tenant in land received in exchange.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37258&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `A landlord may, with the consent of a tenant,`
  line `give in exchange land which is not let, for any land held by such tenant, and such tenant shall have the`
  line `same right in the land so received by him in exchange as he had in the land given in exchange.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (37259)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Exchange of land for consolidation of cultivated area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37259&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person, who wishes to`
  line `consolidate the area which he cultivates, may apply to lie sub-divisional officer to exchange the whole or`
  line `any portion of such area for land cultivated by another person.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on receipt of an application under sub-section (2), the sub-divisional officer is satisfied that`
  line `reasonable grounds exist, he shall grant such application, either in whole or in part, and shall allot to such`
  line `other person land which is cultivated by the applicant and which is approximately equal in value to, and`
  line `of the same quality as, the land received by the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that, to such extent as any land to be exchanged is not approximately equal in value and of`
  line `the same quality, the sub-divisional officer shall award monetary compensation to balance the advantages`
  line `and disadvantages, collect such compensation as arrears of revenue, and pay it to the persons entitled.`
  line
  line `(3) After the order passed under sub-section (2) is complied with, each person shall have, in respect of`
  line `the land which he receives in exchange, the same right as he had in the land which he gives in exchange.`
  line
  line `(4) No order of exchange shall be passed under this section--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of land which is cultivated by a non-occupancy tenant, or is burdened with any`
  line `lease, mortgage or other encumbrance; or`
  line
  line `(b) between persons who are not landlords, or tenants of the same landlord, or who do not stand`
  line `to one another in the relation of landlord and tenant.`
  line
  line `(5) After deciding the case, the sub-divisional officer shall submit the record for confirmation of the`
  line `order passed by him to the collector:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if any area is under record operations, all applications under this section relating to`
  line `such area shall be filed in the court of the record officer.`
  line
  line `(6) If the application is decided by the record officer, the record shall be submitted for confirmation`
  line `of the order passed by him to the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (37260)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Acquisition of land by the landlord for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37260&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) A landlord may apply to the`
  line `collector to acquire for him land held by a tenant for any of the following purposes, namely,--`
  line
  line `(a) for farming on improved lines; or`
  line
  line `(b) for making any water-course, reservoir or tank for irrigation purposes; or`
  line
  line `(c) for opening or working a lime-stone, kankar or other mineral quarry; or`
  line
  line `(d) for undertaking, or allowing any other person to undertake, prospecting work to discover new`
  line `sources of supply of mines and minerals; or`
  line
  line `(e) for the proper working or developing of a mine or mining industry.`
  line
  line `(2) The landlord shall, in case of an application under clause (a), and may, in case of an application`
  line `under any other clause, file a list of his plots available in the same or in a neighbouring village, out of`
  line `which the tenant may make a selection in exchange for the land applied for.`
  line
  line `(3) On getting such application, the collector shall issue a proclamation calling upon persons who`
  line `claim any interest in such land, either as proprietor or otherwise, to file objections, if any, within the`
  line `period specified in the proclamation.`
  line
  line `(4) If the collector is satisfied that reasonable grounds exist, he shall order the acquisition of the land`
  line `applied for, or such part thereof as he deems fit settle the question of compensation in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (5) and (7) and order the ejectment of the tenant from the land acquired.`
  line
  line `(5) The collector, before passing an order of ejectment under sub-section (4), shall proceed as`
  line `follows:--`
  line
  line `(i) if an agreement, which in the opinion of the collector is not unfair is arrived at, he shall give`
  line `effect to it; and`
  line
  line `(ii) failing such agreement he shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of an application under clause (a) of sub-section (1), give to the tenant an option to`
  line `select plots included in the list and allot to him, out of the plots so selected, an area of land`
  line `approximately equal in value to, and of the same quality as, the land acquired; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of an application under clause (b), (c), (d) or (e) of sub-section (1), give to the`
  line `tenant an option to select plots included in the list, if one is filed under sub-section (2), and allot`
  line `to him, out of the plots so selected, an area of land approximately equal in value to, and of the`
  line `same quality as, the land acquired, but if the tenant claims monetary compensation only or if no`
  line `list is filed under sub-section (2), the collector shall award to the tenant monetary compensation`
  line `for his interest in such land; and`
  line
  line `(c) to such extent as the land given in exchange under sub-clause (a) or (b) is not`
  line `approximately equal in value and of the same quality, award monetary compensation to balance`
  line `the advantages and disadvantages.`
  line
  line `(6) If any land is allotted to the tenant under sub-section (5), he shall have the same right in such land`
  line `as he had in the land from which he is ordered to be ejected.`
  line
  line `(7) If as a result of an order of acquisition, the interest of any person, other than the tenant of the land`
  line `to be acquired, is adversely affected, the collector shall award to such person monetary compensation for`
  line `the loss suffered by such person in consequence of such order.`
  line
  line `(8) After deciding the case, the collector shall submit the record for confirmation of the order passed`
  line `by him to the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(9) The amount of monetary compensation awarded under this section shall be recovered as arrears of`
  line `revenue and paid to the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (37261)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Decision of certain disputes arising out of acquisition proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37261&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the course of`
  line `proceedings under section 37, a question of proprietary right arises, the collector shall decide the dispute`
  line `and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the Chief Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that the collector may, if he deems fit, instead of deciding such dispute, grant to any party a`
  line `certificate declaring that the matter is fit to be determined by a civil court and dismiss the application for`
  line `acquisition of land.`
  line
  line `(2) The person to whom such certificate is granted may, within three months of the grant thereof,`
  line `institute a suit to establish his right in a court of competent jurisdiction, and such court may, upon the`
  line `production of such certificate, entertain such suit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a party, to whom such certificate has been granted, fails to institute a suit within the time`
  line `allowed, he shall be deemed to have instituted such suit and lost it.`
  line
  line `(4) The dismissal of an application under the proviso to sub-section (1) shall be no bar to the`
  line `entertainment of a second application for acquisition filed by the landlord, if--`
  line
  line `(i) in the civil suit, instituted under the provisions of the said proviso, the question of proprietary`
  line `right is determined in his favour; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case a certificate to file a suit has been granted to a person other than the landlord, no such`
  line `suit has been filed within the period allowed under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (37262)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Reinstatement of tenant ejected under section 37.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37262&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a tenant is ejected under`
  line `section 57, he shall, on application made to the sub-divisional officer, be entitled to be reinstated in the`
  line `land acquired on the conditions specified in sub-section (3), if the person for whom the land was`
  line acquired--
  line
  line `(a) does not, within two years from the date of such ejectment, use it for the purpose for which it`
  line `was acquired; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses it for any other purpose within a period of five years from the date of such ejectment.`
  line
  line `(2) Such application shall be made--`
  line
  line `in case of clause (a) of sub-section (1), within six months of the expiry of the period of two`
  line `years; and`
  line
  line `in case of clause (b) of sub-section (1), within six months of the land being used for any other`
  line purpose.
  line
  line `(3) The sub-divisional officer, on receiving such application, shall, if the conditions specified in`
  line `clause (a) or (b) of sub-section (1) are satisfied, reinstate the ejected tenant in the land acquired with the`
  line `same rights and liabilities and at the same rate of rent as at the date of ejectment on condition that such`
  line `tenant, before his reinstatement, restores to the person from whom the land was acquired the land or`
  line `money or both awarded to him by way of compensation under section 37.`
  line
  line `(4) After the decision of the case, the sub-divisional officer shall submit the record for confirmation`
  line `of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (37263)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Acquisition of proprietary right by tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37263&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a tenant, other than a non-occupancy tenant,`
  line `desires to acquire proprietary right in his holding, he may apply, in the prescribed form, to the collector`
  line `for acquisition of such right:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such application shall lie in respect of a part of a holding.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of application under sub-section (1), a notice shall be served on the landlord and a copy`
  line `thereof shall be affixed in a prominent place in the village, stating that the tenant of such holding has`
  line `applied for an order of acquisition, and that the landlord or any other person interested in such proceeding`
  line `may file any objections within one month of the affixation of such notice.`
  line
  line `(3) The collector, after deciding the objections filed, shall, if he finds the applicant entitled to`
  line `acquisition, assess the amount of--`
  line
  line `(a) compensation on account of the holding which shall be twelve times the annual rental value of`
  line `such holding, calculated at sanctioned rates applicable to hereditary tenants;`
  line
  line `(b) compensation for any improvement, if any, made by the landlord on such holding; and`
  line
  line `(c) the revenue payable on such holding in the manner prescribed; and`
  line
  line `pass an order that, on payment of such compensation within the period allowed by the collector, the`
  line `tenant shall become the biswadar of his holding and shall be liable to pay the revenue assessed thereon.`
  line
  line `(4) After the decision of the case, the collector shall submit the record of the case for confirmation of`
  line `the order passed by him to the Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(5) The landlord shall, after the tenant has become biswadar, be entitled to claim reduction in the`
  line `revenue payable by him as prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (37264)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Right to written lease and procedure to obtain it.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37264&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tenant of holding shall be entitled`
  line `to receive, from his landholder, a written lease, consistent with the provisions of this Act, drawn up in the`
  line `prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(2) If the lease is not issued to the tenant, or it does not contain the particulars required to be stated`
  line `therein, or contains particulars which the tenant does not accept as correct, he may make an application to`
  line `the tahsildar and claim the lease in the proper form.`
  line
  line `(3) Along with his application the tenant shall file three copies of the draft lease in the prescribed`
  line `form, stating therein all the particulars in accordance with the terms settled between him and his`
  line `landholder, and shall verify each copy as a plaint.`
  line
  line `(4) The tahsildar shall, on receipt of the application, issue notice accompanied by a copy of the lease`
  line `to the landholder to file objections, if any, within the period specified therein.`
  line
  line `(5) If the landholder appears and admits the correctness of the lease, or, after due service of the`
  line `notice, does not appear, the tahsildar shall sign and date the lease, put his official seal on it and deliver it`
  line `to the tenant.`
  line
  line `(6) If the landholder files an objection, the tahsildar shall decide it, and, if the tenant is entitled to a`
  line `lease, deliver the lease in the manner provided by sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) If the lease is delivered to the tenant under sub-section (5) or (6), a true copy thereof shall be`
  line `furnished to the landholder and a copy of such lease shall be placed on the record of the case.`
  line
  line `(8) The tahsildar shall submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him`
  line `under sub-section (6) to the sub-divisional officer.`
  line
  line `(9) A lease so delivered shall be deemed to be registered under the Indian Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (XVI of 1908) and the terms thereof, in so far as they are consistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Act, shall be binding on the parties thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (37265)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Registration of leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37265&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) A lease for a period exceeding one year, or from year to year, or for`
  line `reclaiming any land shall be made by a registered instrument only.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the parties to such lease may, in lieu of`
  line `registering the same, obtain the attestation thereto of a girdawar, a naib-tahsildar, or a tahsildar, within`
  line `whose jurisdiction the land leased is situated in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(3) Such instrument shall be presented for attestation in duplicate.`
  line
  line `(4) The attesting officer shall, after satisfying himself as to the identity of the parties and the`
  line `execution of the instrument, make, sign and date an endorsement thereon to the effect that he has so`
  line `satisfied himself, and shall deliver one copy to the lessor and the other to the lessee:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such instrument shall be accepted for attestation, unless it is presented within four`
  line `months of its execution.`
  line
  line `(5) An instrument so attested shall be deemed to be registered within the meaning of the Indian`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (XVI of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (37266)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Declaration of rights in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37266&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of doubt or dispute, the landholder or the`
  line `tenant may apply for a declaration as to any of the following matters:--`
  line
  line `(i) the rent payable or any other particulars prescribed for the lease;`
  line
  line `(ii) the right of a person claiming to be a tenant or a joint tenant of a holding, or the specification`
  line `of his share in such holding;`
  line
  line `(iii) question of status of a tenant;`
  line
  line `(iv) whether a particular plot is--`
  line
  line `(a) niji jot, or`
  line
  line `(b) stable or unstable land.`
  line
  line `(2) Such application shall be filed in the court of the sub-divisional officer who shall decide the`
  line `dispute in accordance with the provisions of this Act, and submit the record of the case for confirmation`
  line `of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (37267)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Right of certain tenants to make improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37267&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `An occupancy, an exproprietary or a`
  line `hereditary tenant may make any improvement, but he shall not construct a tank unless he has obtained the`
  line `written consent of the landholder.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (37268)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Right of non-occupancy tenants to make improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37268&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No non-occupancy tenant shall`
  line `make any improvement except with the written consent of his landholder:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if such tenant is a sub-tenant, he shall not make any improvement unless--`
  line
  line `(a) it is an improvement which his landholder could himself have made; and`
  line
  line `(b) he has obtained the written consent of his landholder.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (37269)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Right of landlord to make Improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37269&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) A landlord may, with the sanction of the`
  line `sub-divisional officer, make an improvement on, or affecting, the holding of a tenant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such sanction shall be required if the tenant of such holding is a non-occupancy`
  line `tenant, or the improvement which the landlord desires to make is a well.`
  line
  line `(2) If the sub-divisional officer refuses to give sanction, he shall submit the record of the case for`
  line `confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (37270)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Provision when both landlord and tenant want to make the same improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37270&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) If both`
  line `the landlord and the tenant want to make the same improvement which they are entitled to make under`
  line `this Act, the sub-divisional officer shall, on application, allow the tenant to execute the work within a`
  line `specified period and may, on reasonable cause being shown, extend such period from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total period of such extensions shall not exceed six months.`
  line
  line `(2) If the tenant fails to execute the work within such period or extended period, the landlord shall`
  line `have the right to make such improvement.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (37271)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Restrictions on making improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37271&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall-entitle a tenant or a`
  line `landholder to make an improvement on, or detrimental to, any land, not included in the holding to be`
  line `benefited by such improvement, unless he is in possession of such land as owner, or has obtained the`
  line `written consent of the landlord and of the tenant, if any, of such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (37272)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Compensation for improvement, when permissible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37272&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `A tenant who has made a work of the`
  line `kind to which the provisions of clause (13) of section 4 apply, whether such work was made before or`
  line `after the commencement of this Act, shall be entitled to claim compensation--`
  line
  line `(a) if an order of ejectment is passed against him; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he has been wrongfully ejected from his land and has not recovered possession thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a dwelling house mentioned in sub-clause (i) of clause (13) of section 4, the`
  line `tenant may, instead of claiming compensation, sell or remove the materials thereof or, with the written`
  line `consent of the landlord and within such period as the court deciding the claim for compensation may`
  line `specify, transfer the right of residence therein to any tenant of the village:`
  line
  line `Provided further that except in case of such dwelling house, compensation shall not be payable for`
  line `any work made more than thirty years prior to the date on which the order of ejectment was passed or the`
  line `tenant was wrongfully ejected.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (37273)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Determination of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37273&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `When, under any provision of this Act, a court has to`
  line `determine the amount of compensation due on account of an improvement, it shall have regard--`
  line
  line `(a) to the amount by which the value or the produce of the holding, or the value of that produce,`
  line `is increased by the work,`
  line
  line `(b) to the condition of such work and the probable duration of its effect,`
  line
  line `(c) to the extent or benefit to which the landholder or the tenant may be entitled under`
  line `section 51, and`
  line
  line `(d) to the labour and capital required for the making of such work, allowing for--`
  line
  line `(i) any reduction or remission of rent or any other advantage allowed to the tenant by the`
  line `landholder in consideration of the work,`
  line
  line `(ii) any assistance given to the tenant by the landholder in money, material or labour, and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of reclamation or of conversion of unirrigated to irrigated land, the length of`
  line `time during which the party claiming compensation has had the benefit of the improvement.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (37274)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Works benefiting other land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37274&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a tenant has made an improvement on land from which he`
  line `is ejected, the landholder shall, on payment of compensation, if awarded, become the owner of the work,`
  line `but the tenant shall be entitled to the benefit of the work in respect of the land remaining in his possession`
  line `to the same extent and in the same manner as it was hitherto benefited thereby.`
  line
  line `(2) If a tenant has made an improvement on land which remains in his possession after he is ejected`
  line `from the other portion of his holding, the landholder shall, in accordance with the conditions laid down by`
  line `the court, be entitled to the benefit of such work in respect of the land from which the tenant has been`
  line `ejected to the same extent and in the same manner as it was hitherto benefited thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (37275)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Disputes as regards improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37275&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If a question arises between a tenant and his landholder--`
  line
  line `(a) as to the right to make an improvement; or`
  line
  line `(b) as to whether a work contravenes the provisions of section 48; or`
  line
  line `(c) as to whether a particular work is an improvement; or`
  line
  line `(d) as to the right to the benefit of an improvement under section 51,`
  line
  line `the sub-divisional officer shall, on the application of either party, decide the question and submit the`
  line `record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (37276)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Right of tenant paying fixed money rent to plant tree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37276&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `A tenant, other than a non-occupancy`
  line `tenant, who pays fixed money rent may plant on his Molding any tree:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall not plant any tree in such a way as to diminish the value of any land, not included in`
  line `his holding; and`
  line
  line `(b) he shall, in the absence of a written agreement to the contrary, continue to be liable to pay the`
  line `full rent of the holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (37277)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Right of a tenant paying batai or bighori to plant tree.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37277&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `A tenant, other than a non-occupancy`
  line `tenant, who pays rent by batai, or bighori or partly by batai and partly by bighori, may plant any tree with`
  line `the written consent of his landlord on such terms as may be settled between them:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not plant any tree in such a way as to diminish the value of any land, not`
  line `included in his holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (37278)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Tenant's rights in tree existing at the commencement of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37278&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any tree standing at the`
  line `commencement of this Act on the holding of a tenant, not being a sub-tenant, shall vest in such tenant, if`
  line `he has continuously been in possession of such holding for not less than twelve years immediately before`
  line `such commencement.`
  line
  line `(2) If a tree does not vest in such tenant under sub-section (1), he may--`
  line
  line `(i) if such tree hinders the cultivation of the folding, fell it with the previous sanction of the`
  line `tahsildar and after notice in writing to the landlord or his agent, and deliver the timber thereof to such`
  line `landlord or agent; or`
  line
  line `(ii) appropriate such tree and pay to the landholder such price as the tahsildar may, on the`
  line `application of the tenant, fix.`
  line
  line `(3) The tahsildar shall, if the order giving or refusing sanction for felling, such tree or fixing the price`
  line `thereof is passed in a contested case, submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by`
  line `him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (37279)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Decision of disputes regarding trees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37279&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If a dispute arises between a landlord and a tenant as to`
  line `the right to plant any tree, or the manner of planting it, or regarding the ownership of any tree, the dispute`
  line `shall, on the application of either party, be decided by the sub-divisional officer who shall submit the`
  line `record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (37280)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Surrender by tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37280&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 29, a tenant, not bound by a lease or`
  line `other agreement to continue to occupy any holding in the following year, may--`
  line
  line `(i) by means of a registered letter, sent to his landholder before the first day of March in any year,`
  line `notify his intention to surrender his holding at the end of the agricultural year, whether such holding,`
  line `is or is not held by a sub-tenant; and`
  line
  line `(ii) surrender his holding by giving up possession thereof accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that an exproprietary tenant shall not surrender his holding of any part thereof except to his`
  line `own landholder, and unless (a) a period of two years has elapsed from the date of accrual of the`
  line `exproprietary rights, and (b) such tenant has obtained the previous sanction of the collector:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall affect any arrangement by which a tenant, other than`
  line `an exproprietary tenant, and the landholder may agree to the surrender of the whole or any portion of the`
  line holding.
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (37281)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title Abandonment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37281&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) a tenant who ceases to`
  line `cultivate his holding and leaves the neighbourhood, shall not lose his interest in such holding, if he leaves`
  line `in charge thereof a person responsible for payment of the rent as it falls due and gives written notice to the`
  line `landholder of such arrangement.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person so left in charge is a person--`
  line
  line `(a) on whom, in the event of the tenant's death, the tenant's interest would devolve, or`
  line
  line `(b) who is to manage the holding for the benefit of the person on whom in the event of the`
  line `tenants death, the tenants interest would devolve,`
  line
  line `the tenant shall, on the expiry of a period of seven years, lose his interest in his holding unless he, within`
  line `such period, resumes cultivation thereof, and such interest shall devolve on the person on whom the`
  line `interest of the tenant would devolve in the event of his death.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person so left in charge is not a person mentioned in sub-section (2), the tenant shall, on the`
  line `expiry of a period of three years, be deemed to have abandoned his holding, unless within such period he`
  line `resumes cultivation thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) A tenant who ceases to cultivate and leaves the neighbourhood, otherwise than in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (2), shall be deemed to have abandoned his holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (37282)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Taking possession of holding surrendered or abandoned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37282&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `A landholder may enter upon, and`
  line `occupy, the land surrendered or abandoned in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (37283)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Dispute arising out of surrender and abandonment of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37283&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a dispute arises as to--`
  line
  line `(a) the right of a tenant to surrender his holding or part thereof, or`
  line
  line `(b) the right of a landholder to enter upon and occupy the land under the provisions of section 59,`
  line
  line `either party may, within three months from the date of such dispute, apply to the tahsildar for decision.`
  line
  line `(2) The tahsildar shall decide the dispute and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the`
  line `order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (37284)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Acceptance of premium; how far permissible.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37284&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `No landholder shall accept a premium for`
  line `admitting a person to a holding:`
  line
  line `Provided that this prohibition shall not apply to a landlord who confers biswadari right in any waste`
  line `or unimproved land or common land of a village.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (37285)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Lag, neg and cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37285&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding any custom or contract to the contrary, no lag, or neg,`
  line `by whatever name called or known, shall, in addition to the rent of the holding, be levied on, or recovered`
  line `from, a tenant:`
  line
  line `Provided that this prohibition shall not apply to a village development cess levied under`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, declare that`
  line `the tenants of any village shall be liable to pay a village development cess, not exceeding two and a half`
  line `per cent, of the rental to be applied for such purposes, and to be collected and disbursed in such manner,`
  line `as may be prescribed in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of doubt, the Chief Commissioner may determine whether any levy is a levy prohibited by`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (37286)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Liability for payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37286&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Every occupancy, exproprietory, hereditary or non-occupancy`
  line `tenant shall be liable to pay rent in accordance with the provisions of section 64:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, at the commencement of this Act, a lower rent is payable by a tenant, or, after such`
  line `commencement, a lower rent is agreed upon between him and his landholder, he shall be liable to pay`
  line `such rent only.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (37287)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Scale of rent for different classes of tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37287&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 63, a tenant`
  line `shall be liable to pay rent in accordance with the following scale:--`
  line
  line `(a) a hereditary or a non-occupancy tenant, other than a`
  line sub-tenant
  line `one-fifth of the produce of his holding;`
  line
  line `(b) an occupancy tenant one-sixth of the produce of his holding;`
  line
  line `(c) an exproprietary tenant one-eighth of the produce of his holding:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in any area bighori at customary rate is payable for any crop, a tenant may elect to`
  line `pay such rate for such crop:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if a tenant grows cotton, or a crop in which cotton predominates, on more than`
  line `one fourth of the irrigable area of his holding, the rent of such excess area shall be payable at double the`
  line `bighori at customary rates.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section the expression "produce of his holding" shall not include the straw`
  line `chaff (bhusa) of the rabi or the dry stalks of kharif crop.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (37288)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Status and liability of person permitted to retain possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37288&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 106, a person occupying any vacant land in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall, if permitted in writing by the landlord to retain possession of such land, become a hereditary`
  line `tenant thereof and shall be liable to pay rent in accordance with the provisions of sections 63 and 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (37289)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Hypothecation of produce towards payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37289&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `The produce of every holding, whether`
  line `sub-let or not, shall be deemed to be hypothecated of the landlord for the rent payable in respect of such`
  line `holding and, until the demand for such rent has been satisfied, no other claim on such produce shall be`
  line `enforced by sale in execution of a decree of a civil or revenue court, or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (37290)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Procedure when produce is attached by civil or revenue court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37290&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the produce of any`
  line `holding is attached by an order of a civil or revenue court, such court shall give notice of such attachment`
  line `to the landlord who may apply to such court to sell the produce and pay to him, out of the proceeds of the`
  line `sale thereof, any arrears of rent due in respect of such holding up to the date of the attachment.`
  line
  line `(2) If such court, on inquiry, finds the landlord's claim to the whole or any part of the rent to be`
  line `proved, it shall sell the produce or such portion thereof as it may deem fit, and apply the proceeds of the`
  line `sale, in the first instance, to satisfy such claim.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (37291)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Right of landlord to collect rent from cultivator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37291&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the rent of a holding which is sub-let,`
  line `or is left in charge of another person under section 58, is payable to the landlord by batai, he may collect`
  line `such rent from the sub-tenant or such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any rent is so collected by the landlord, the sub-tenant may deduct such rent from any`
  line `rent payable by him to his landholder.`
  line
  line `(2) If any conflict arises between the claims of the landlord and the tenant of such holding to collect`
  line `rent from the sub-tenant the claim of the landlord shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (37292)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `No cartage allowed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37292&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `When rent is paid by batai, the landholder shall not claim or receive any`
  line `additional quantity of the produce or its money equivalent for cartage to his own residence or to any`
  line `market place.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (37293)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Presumption as to payment by tenant and application of such payment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37293&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `If a tenant makes a`
  line `payment to his landholder, the payment shall, in the absence of a direction to the contrary, be deemed to`
  line `have been made on account of rent, and shall be credited to any year, instalment or holding, specified by`
  line `the tenant:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such payment shall be applied to the discharge of an arrear of rent which has been`
  line `outstanding for more than two years at the date of such payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (37294)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Modes of making payment of money rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37294&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) A payment of a money rent may be made by a`
  line `tenant to his landholder, either direct or by money order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the acceptance by a landholder of a sum paid by money-order shall not, by itself or by`
  line `virtue of anything written on the money-order form, be deemed to constitute an admission by him as to`
  line `the amount of rent payable or due on account of any particular year, instalment or holding, or an`
  line `admission that the payer is a tenant.`
  line
  line `(2) When such rent is sent by money order, in the case of acceptance, the payee's receipt and in the`
  line `case of refusal, the endorsement of such refusal on the money-order form, duly stamped by the post`
  line `office, shall be admissible in evidence without formal proof and shall, until the contrary is proved, be`
  line `presumed to be a correct record of such acceptance or refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (37295)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Right to get receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37295&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every tenant, lessee or licensee who makes payment on account of`
  line `rent, sayar or premium shall be entitled to obtain forthwith from the landholder a written receipt signed`
  line `by the landholder or his agent.`
  line
  line `(2) The landholder shall, from a book printed under section 74, give a separate receipt for each sum`
  line `paid on account of rent, sayar or premium, and shall prepare and retain a counterfoil of each receipt given`
  line `by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (37296)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Penalty for not issuing proper receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37296&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `If a receipt is not issued in the prescribed form, or does`
  line `not contain substantially the particulars required to be stated therein, or if a joint receipt for rent, sayar or`
  line `premium has been given in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 72, it shall be`
  line `presumed, until the contrary is proved, to be an acquittance in full of all demands for rent, sayar, or`
  line `premium, as the case may be, up to the date on which the receipt was given.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (37297)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Obligation of Chief Commissioner to print and supply books of receipt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37297&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner shall cause to be printed and kept for sale to landholders, at all tahsil headquarters, books`
  line `of receipts with counterfoils in the prescribed form at a rate, not exceeding the actual cost of production,`
  line `plus five per cent, thereon to cover incidental charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (37298)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Penalty for non-production of receipt book with counterfoils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37298&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `If, in any proceeding under`
  line `this Act between a landholder and a tenant in which the payment of rent, sayar or premium is in dispute,`
  line `the landholder, when ordered by the court to produce the book of receipts with counterfoils which he is`
  line `required to retain under section 72, fails to produce it, the court may accept the plea of the tenant`
  line `regarding such payment as correct or may make any presumption against the landholder which it`
  line `considers reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (37299)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Rights and liabilities in respect of produce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37299&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) When rent is payable by batai, the tenant shall`
  line `have a right to the exclusive possession of the crop and to cut and harvest it in due course of husbandry`
  line `without any interference on the part of the landholder, but shall not be entitled to cut any portion of the`
  line `produce of his holding or to remove it from the threshing-floor at such time or in such manner as to`
  line `prevent the due division thereof at the proper time.`
  line
  line `(2) If a landholder prevents a tenant from tending, cutting, gathering or storing the crop, or otherwise`
  line `interferes with harvesting operations, he shall be liable, on the complaint of the tenant, to pay to him such`
  line `sum, not exceeding one hundred rupees, as may be awarded as compensation and such sum shall be`
  line `recovered as arrears of revenue and paid to the tenant.`
  line
  line `(3) Such complaint shall be made in writing to the sub-divisional officer who shall inquire into, and`
  line `decide, the case and submit the record for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(4) If the tenant cuts or removes any portion of the produce of his holding, contrary to the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (1), such produce shall, for the purpose of determining the share of the landholder, be`
  line `deemed to be equal to that of the best crop of the same kind grown at that harvest on similar land in the`
  line neighbourhood.
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (37300)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Application for officer to make division.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37300&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the rent of any land is payable by batai,`
  line `the tenant may, when the crop is ripe, apply to the tahsildar, requesting that an officer be deputed to make`
  line `the division and, subject to the payment of the prescribed fee, the tahsildar shall, within ten days of such`
  line `payment, depute an officer for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The officer so deputed shall proceed to the spot on a day of which notice shall be given to the`
  line `landholder and the tenant, cause the crop to be cut or gathered, and stored, and, after such inquiry as he`
  line `deems fit, get the produce divided in accordance with the shares to which the parties may be respectively`
  line entitled.
  line
  line `(3) The weighment charges or other expenses, if any, incurred in making the division shall be borne`
  line `by the parties in proportion to their shares in the produce.`
  line
  line `(4) In making the division, such officer shall take the assistance of assessors to be appointed, as`
  line `nearly as may be, in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 79, draw up a`
  line `note specifying the share of produce delivered to each party and other necessary particulars, explain such`
  line `note to the parties and assessors, get it signed by them and submit it with his report to the tahsildar.`
  line
  line `(5) Such officer shall not allow any levy prohibited by sub-section (1) of section 62 to be charged at`
  line `the time of batai, and in his report to the tahsildar he shall state that no such levy was charged.`
  line
  line `(6) If either the landholder or the tenant is dissatisfied with the division he may, within fifteen days of`
  line `such division, complain in writing to the tahsildar who shall inquire into the matter and, if necessary, pass`
  line `a decree for money in favour of the party entitled, and submit the record of the case for confirmation of`
  line `the decree or order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer If no such complaint is made, the tahsildar`
  line `shall confirm the note of the officer deputed.`
  line
  line `(7) The sub-divisional officer may confirm, amend or set aside the decree of order or pass such other`
  line `order as he deems fit.`
  line
  line `(8) A decree for money passed under sub-section (6) or (7) shall, if against the tenant, be deemed to`
  line `be a decree for arrears of rent and, if against the landholder, be realised in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of sections 88 and 89.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (37301)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Application for kuta.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37301&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `If, by an agreement between a landholder and his tenant, the batai rent of`
  line `a holding is payable in cash by kuta, either party may apply in the prescribed form to the tahsildar to`
  line `depute an officer to make the kuta.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (37302)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37302&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application under section 78, and on payment`
  line `of the prescribed fee, the tahsildar shall, within ten days of such payment, issue a written notice to the`
  line `landholder and the tenant to attend on such date and at such time and place as may be specified in the`
  line `notice, and shall depute an officer by whom the kuta shall be made.`
  line
  line `(2) On the day, and at the time and place, so fixed, such officer shall attend and call upon each party`
  line `to appoint a resident of the neighbourhood as an assessor to assist him.`
  line
  line `(3) If any party fails to attend, or refuses to appoint an assessor, sum officer shall appoint an assessor`
  line `on his behalf and shall, with the assistance of the assessors so appointed, make the kuta and deliver an`
  line `award in the prescribed form and submit the same with a report of the proceedings to the tahsildar.`
  line
  line `(4) The tahsildar shall issue notice to the parties to file objections, if any, to the award within fifteen`
  line `days of the date of service of such notice and shall, after hearing such objections and making such`
  line `inquiry, as he considers necessary, accept or modify such award and submit the record of the case for`
  line `confirmation of the order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
  line
  line `(5) The sub-divisional officer may, after further inquiry, if necessary, confirm or modify the award.`
  line
  line `(6) After the award has become final, the tahsildar shall assess the money value of the rent payable to`
  line `the landholder and pass a decree for arrears of rent against the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (37303)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Collector to publish return of current prices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37303&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Within one month of the end of harvesting`
  line `operations in a tahsil, or as soon thereafter as may be, the collector shall prepare, in the prescribed`
  line `manner, a return of market prices current at the harvest time of all food and non-food crops grown in such`
  line `tahsil and the return so prepared shall be accepted for assessing the money value of the produce of a`
  line `holding in cases triable under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in any area, the Central Government has fixed any price for any agricultural produce`
  line `such price shall be accepted for making such assessment.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (37304)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Assessment of bighori by court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37304&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of bighori--`
  line
  line `(a) if the landholder or the tenant neglects to measure the area sown at the proper time, or`
  line
  line `(b) if there is a dispute about the extent of the area sown, the length of the measuring chain, or the`
  line `manner of measurement of such area,`
  line
  line `either party may make an application to the tahsildar, requesting that a measurer be appointed to measure`
  line `such area.`
  line
  line `With the application, the applicant shall deposit such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (1) to (3) of section 79 shall apply to an application made under`
  line `this section, as if for the words "kuta" and "officer", wherever they occur in such sub-sections, the words`
  line `"measurement" and "measurer" respectively were substituted.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the measurer's award, the tahsildar shall issue notice to the parties to file objections,`
  line `if any, within fifteen days of the date of service of such notice and, after hearing such objections, pass a`
  line `decree for the arrears of rent found due, and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the decree`
  line `passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (37305)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Commutation of batai rent into bighori in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37305&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a tenant, other than a`
  line `non-occupancy tenant, has heretofore paid his rent by batai, or partly by bighori and partly by batai, he`
  line `may, apply to the sub-divisional officer to commute his rent paid by batai into bighori.`
  line
  line `(2) The sub-divisional officer shall, in accordance with the table of rates prepared in the prescribed`
  line `manner, declare the bighori which such tenant shall be liable to pay.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (37306)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Payment of commuted rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37306&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The rent commuted under the provisions of section 82 shall`
  line `become payable from June next following the date of the order and shall remain in force for three`
  line `agricultural years unless, at the end of such period, the landlord and the tenant, by a joint application`
  line `made to the sub-divisional officer, get the period extended for any term agreed upon between them.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (37307)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Rent when and how payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37307&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the rent of a tenant shall`
  line `be payable as follows:--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of batai or bighori--`
  line
  line `(a) as agreed upon between the tenant and the landholder,`
  line
  line `(b) in the absence of any such agreement, according to local custom, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of fixed money rent, in instalments proportionate to the revenue instalments payable`
  line `one month before the dates appointed for the payment of the revenue instalments.`
  line
  line `(2) Rent, or any instalment thereof, not paid by due date, shall be deemed to be in arrears.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (37308)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Claim for arrears of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37308&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) If rent, which is payable by batai or bighori, is in arrears, or if`
  line `the tenant has, without sufficient cause, failed to cultivate his holding, the landholder may, within two`
  line `years of the date on which rent became payable, apply to the tahsildar for the recovery of arrears of rent.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for the recovery of fixed money-rent shall be made to the tahsildar within two`
  line `years of the date on which such rent became payable.`
  line
  line `(3) For purposes of the assessment of the rent recoverable under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of batai, the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 76 shall apply, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of batai or bighori, the entire area of the holding of the defendant shall, in the absence`
  line `of evidence to the contrary, be deemed to have been actually cultivated during the period to which the`
  line `claim relates.`
  line
  line `(4) The tahsildar shall decide the case and submit the record for confirmation of the decree passed by`
  line `him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (37309)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Interest in cases of arrears of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37309&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `When a court passes a decree for arrears of rent under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, it shall allow interest on the amount decreed from the date of such decree till`
  line `the date of its satisfaction at the rate of one anna per rupee per annum simple interest unless, for reasons`
  line `to be recorded in writing, it disallows the interest or allows interest at a lower rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (37310)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Landlord's power to charge irrigation dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37310&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `If a landlord has constructed a tank, whether`
  line `before or after the commencement of this Act, he shall, subject to the rules made by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner, be entitled to charge irrigation dues from persons irrigating land from such tank, at such`
  line `rates as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (37311)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Method of recovering sayar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37311&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) A landlord to whom any sum is due on account of sayar may,`
  line `on an application to the tahsildar, recover the same by attachment and sale of the property of the defaulter`
  line `with the exception of the following:--`
  line
  line `(a) the necessary wearing apparel, cooking utensils, beds and bedding of the defaulter, and of his`
  line `wife and children and such personal ornaments as, in accordance with religious usage, cannot be`
  line `parted with by any woman;`
  line
  line `(b) his implements of husbandry and such cattle and seed grain as may, in the opinion of the`
  line `court, be necessary to enable him to earn his livelihood as an agriculturist; and`
  line
  line `(c) houses and other buildings belonging to the defaulter and actually occupied by him or used by`
  line `him as a cattle-shed.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the course of any proceeding under sub-section (1), any claim is preferred to, or any`
  line `objection is made to the attachment of, any property by any person, whether a party to such proceeding or`
  line `not, the tahsildar shall decide the dispute and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order`
  line `passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (37312)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Realisation of sayar as arrears of revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37312&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the opinion of the tahsildar the arrears of`
  line `sayar cannot be recovered under section 88, he may move the sub-divisional officer to sanction the`
  line `collection of such arrears as arrears of revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) The sub-divisional officer may, if he is satisfied that such arrears cannot be recovered under`
  line `section 88, direct the tahsildar to recover such arrears as arrears of revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) Any arrears of sayar recovered under section 88 or under this section shall be paid by the`
  line `tahsildar to the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (37313)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Recovery of arrears in the event of general refusal to pay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37313&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of any general refusal`
  line `to pay rent or any demand on account of sayar to persons entitled to collect the same in any area, the`
  line `Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that such rent or demand may be`
  line `recovered in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) In any area to which a notification made under sub-section (1) applies, a landholder entitled to`
  line `collect such rent or demand may, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, apply in writing to the tahsildar to recover the same, and the`
  line `tahsildar shall, after satisfying himself that the amount claimed is due, recover file same with costs as`
  line `arrears of revenue and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the orders passed, and the action`
  line `taken, by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(3) The collector may, after examining the record, order that, after deducting from the amount`
  line `recovered the collection charges which shall not ordinarily exceed seven per cent, of the amount so`
  line `recovered, the balance shall be made ever to the person entitled:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount deducted as court-fee under section 178 and collection charges shall`
  line `not, in the aggregate, exceed fourteen and a half per cent, of the amount so recovered.`
  line
  line `(4) No order passed under this section shall debar a landholder from recovering, under the provisions`
  line `of this Act, any amount due to him which has not been recovered under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (37314)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Application of certain sections to biswadars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37314&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of sections 62, 66, 67, 69 to`
  line `77, 81, 87 to 90 and 108 to 112 shall apply to a biswadar in relation to a jagirdar or a muafidar, as if in`
  line `such sections for the word "tenant", the word "biswadar" and for the word "landlord" or "landholder" the`
  line `word "jagirdar" or "muafidar", as the ease may be, and for the word "rent" the words "revenue payable by`
  line `a biswadar", were substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of a decree for arrears of revenue passed against a biswadar, if not satisfied within`
  line `thirty days of the date when such decree becomes final shall, on the application of the decree-holder, be`
  line `recovered by the tahsildar as arrears of revenue and paid to the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (37315)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Arrears deemed satisfied when tenant is ejected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37315&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 94, when a tenant is ejected from his holding for non-payment of arrears of rent, all arrears,`
  line `whether decreed or not, and irrigation dues due in respect of such holding on the date of ejectment shall`
  line `be deemed to have been satisfied.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (37316)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Decree for arrears, how executed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37316&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `No decree for arrears of rent shall be executed against a`
  line `tenant otherwise than in the manner provided by section 98.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (37317)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Adjustment of arrears and compensation on ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37317&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) A court, deciding any proceeding`
  line `under this Act by which a tenant is ejected from his holding or part thereof shall, before passing an order`
  line `of ejectment, award the amount of compensation due to him on account of an improvement, a tree or a`
  line `crop belonging to him and existing on such holding:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, on the date of such order, no arrears of rent, decreed or undecreed, or irrigation dues`
  line `are outstanding against him on account of such holding and there is a tree or crop upon the land, he may`
  line `cut and remove such tree and, subject to such payment and such other terms as the court passing the order`
  line `may specify, use such land for tending, gathering and removing such crop.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on such date, any such arrears are outstanding against the tenant and the amount of`
  line `compensation awarded to him under sub-section (1) exceeds the amount recoverable from him as such`
  line `arrears, the order for ejectment shall be conditional on the payment into court by the landholder of the`
  line `balance due to the tenant within such time as the court may direct; and if the amount of such`
  line `compensation does not exceed such arrears, any claim for compensation made by the tenant shall be`
  line `deemed to have been satisfied on his ejectment.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (37318)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Entry of landholder on land from which tenant is ordered to be ejected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37318&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) A landholder`
  line `may enter upon possession of a holding or part thereof from which a tenant is ordered to be ejected:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not enter upon such holding or part unless--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case to which the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 94 applies, the tenant has gathered`
  line `and removed the crop in due course of husbandry; and`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of compensation, if any, awarded by the court has been paid into court or adjusted`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 94.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount of compensation awarded under sub-section (1) of section 94 has not been paid into`
  line `court or adjusted in accordance with sub-section (2) of that section, the order of ejectment shall be`
  line `cancelled, and the landholder shall be liable to pay to the tenant the cost of the proceedings which shall be`
  line `collected as arrears of revenue and paid to the tenant.`
  line
  line `(3) If the tenant offers any resistance or obstruction to entry on land on which a landholder has`
  line `become entitled to enter under sub-section (1), the court passing the order of ejectment shall, on the`
  line `application of the landholder, direct that such landholder be put into possession of such land and where he`
  line `is still resisted or obstructed in obtaining possession, the court may, at his instance, order the tenant to be`
  line `detained in the civil prison under rule 98 of Order XXI of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (V of 1908).`
  line
  line `(4) The court hearing any proceeding by which a tenant is ejected from his holding or part thereof`
  line `shall decide all disputes arising under section 94 or this section and such decision shall be subject to`
  line `confirmation by the court to which the record of such proceeding is submitted for confirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (37319)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Grounds of ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37319&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `A tenant shall be liable to ejectment from his holding on one or more of`
  line `the following grounds:--`
  line
  line `(a) that a final decree against him for arrears of rent in respect of that holding had remained`
  line `unsatisfied; or`
  line
  line `(b) that he is guilty of any act detrimental to the land in that holding, or inconsistent with the`
  line `purpose for which it was let; or`
  line
  line `(c) where rent is payable by batai, that for three successive years he has, without sufficient cause,`
  line `failed to cultivate his holding; or`
  line
  line `(d) that he or any person holding from him has broken a condition on breach of which he is, by`
  line `special contract which is not contrary to the provisions of section 8, liable to be ejected; or`
  line
  line `(e) that he has sub-let or otherwise transferred his holding or part thereof in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the use of one-twentieth part of a plot included in a holding for growing grass or for the`
  line `construction of enclosures on such part for stock raising, or for any purpose subservient to agriculture,`
  line `shall not constitute a ground for ejectment under clause (b).`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (37320)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Special grounds of ejectment of non-occupancy tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37320&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `A non-occupancy tenant, other than`
  line `a sub-tenant to whom the provisions of section 32 apply, shall be liable to ejectment on the ground that he`
  line `holds only as a tenant from year to year, or under a lease which has expired or will expire by the end of`
  line `the current agricultural year.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (37321)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Procedure in ejectment for decreed arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37321&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) Immediately after a decree for arrears of rent`
  line `passed under section 77, 79, 81 or 85 has become final, the tahsildar shall cause a notice to be served on`
  line `the tenant stating the amount due under the decree, and requiring him, within two months from the service`
  line `of the notice, to pay such amount into court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount is so paid, the tahsildar shall record satisfaction on the decree and grant a receipt`
  line `therefore which shall operate as an acquittance for the amount deposited as if such amount had been`
  line `received by the decree holder and pay such amount to the person entitled to receive it.`
  line
  line `(3) If the amount is not so paid by the tenant the tahsildar shall order his ejectment from his holding`
  line `or part thereof as prescribed and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him`
  line `to the sub-divisional officer.`
  line
  line `(4) The sub-divisional officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) on the application of the tenant, extend the tithe for the payment of the decretal amount for a`
  line `period, not exceeding two months from the date of such order; or`
  line
  line `(b) allow payment into court of such amount by installments and specify the time for payment`
  line `thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) confirm the order of ejectment.`
  line
  line `(5) If the sub-divisional officer by order extends the time for the payment of the decretal amount or`
  line `allows payment by installments and such order is duly complied with, the order of ejectment shall be set`
  line aside.
  line
  line `(6) If the decretal amount or any installment is not paid into court within the period allowed under`
  line `clause (a) or (b) of sub-section (4), the sub-divisional officer shall confirm the order of ejectment.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (37322)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Procedure for ejectment on other grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37322&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a landholder desires to eject a tenant on`
  line `one or more of the grounds specified in clauses (b) to (c) of section 96, he shall file an application in the`
  line `court of the sub-divisional officer containing such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If the sub-divisional officer finds that the tenants is liable to ejectment, he shall pass a conditional`
  line `order for his ejectment either from the entire holding or from such portion thereof, as, having regard to all`
  line `the circumstances of the case, he considers desirable and shall also direct that--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an order under clause (b), (c) or (d) of section 96, the tenant shall repair the`
  line `damage, or pay such compensation as the court may direct within two months from the date of the`
  line `order, or such further time as the court may, for reasons to be recorded allow; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an order under clause (e) of that section, the tenant shall obtain surrender of, or`
  line `eject the sub-lessee or other transferee from, the holding or part thereof which is sub-let or otherwise`
  line `transferred in contravention of the provisions of this Act and resume possession of such holding or`
  line `part, as the case may be, within such time as the court may specify.`
  line
  line `(3) If the sub-divisional officer is satisfied that the tenant has complied with the order passed under`
  line `sub-section (2), he shall cancel the order of ejectment, but if he is not so satisfied, he shall make the order`
  line `of ejectment absolute and shall, in either case, submit the record for confirmation of the order passed by`
  line `him to the collector:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for ejectment shall be entertained on the ground mentioned in clause (c)`
  line `of section 96, if the landholder has recovered under section 85 the arrears of rent for the period the tenant`
  line `has failed to cultivate his holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (37323)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Application for ejectment of non-occupancy tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37323&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `A landholder who desires to eject a`
  line `non-occupancy tenant to whom section 97 applies may, in the month of May, make an application in`
  line `duplicate to the tahsildar stating the following particulars:--`
  line
  line `(a) the name, description and place of residence of the landholder;`
  line
  line `(b) the name, description and place of residence of the tenant;`
  line
  line `(c) a description of the holding, specifying the name of the village, the rent payable, and, unless`
  line `the holding can be otherwise adequately described, the khasra number and area of each field; and`
  line
  line `(d) the ground on which ejectment is applied for.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (37324)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37324&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The tahsildar shall send one copy of the application to the`
  line `tenant and inform him that he may file objections, if any, within thirty days of the receipt of such`
  line application.
  line
  line `(2) It the tenant admits his liability to ejectment, or has not appeared within such period, the tahsildar`
  line `shall pass an order for his ejectment.`
  line
  line `(3) If the tenant contests his liability to ejectment on the ground that he is not a tenant, or claims`
  line `occupancy, exproprietary or hereditary rights, or denies the right of the landholder to eject, the tahsildar`
  line `shall forward the record to the sub-divisional officer for trial of the case.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of the record, the sub-divisional officer shall hear and decide the case and submit the`
  line `record for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(5) If the liability to ejectment is contested on any other ground, the tahsildar shall decide the case`
  line `and submit the record for confirmation of the order passed by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (37325)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Remedies for wrongful ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37325&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `A tenant ejected by his landholder, otherwise than in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act may, within one year of such ejectment, apply to the`
  line `sub-divisional officer--`
  line
  line `(a) for possession of the holding;`
  line
  line `(b) for compensation for wrongful dispossession; and`
  line
  line `(c) for compensation for any improvement he may have made, or for a tree belonging to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (37326)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37326&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the court finds that the tenant has been wrongfully ejected, it`
  line `shall proceed as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the tenant is not entitled to remain in possession after the expiry of the agricultural year in`
  line `which the order is passed, the order shall not be for recovery of possession, but for costs only, or, if`
  line `compensation has been claimed and found due, for compensation and costs only;`
  line
  line `(b) when the order is for recovery of possession, compensation, if claimed and found due, may be`
  line `awarded for wrongful dispossession but not for an improvement or a tree;`
  line
  line `(c) where an order is given for compensation for wrongful dispossession, but not for possession,`
  line `the compensation shall be for the whole period during which the tenant was entitled to remain in`
  line possession.
  line
  line `(2) If the order is for recovery of possession, the sub-divisional officer shall put the tenant wrongfully`
  line `ejected in possession.`
  line
  line `(3) After the decision of the case, the sub-divisional officer shall submit the record for confirmation`
  line `of the order passed by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(4) Any amount awarded as compensation shall be recovered as arrears of revenue and paid to the`
  line `person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (37327)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Ejectment of person occupying land without title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37327&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person, other than a landholder`
  line `mentioned in section 102, taking or retaining possession of a plot of land otherwise than in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act shall, on the application made to the sub-divisional officer, be liable to`
  line `ejectment and also to pay damages.`
  line
  line `(2) Such application shall be made--`
  line
  line `(a) if the unauthorised occupation has existed from a date prior to the commencement of this Act,`
  line `within two years of the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, within three years from the date when the unauthorised occupation first`
  line began.
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (37328)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Procedure on application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37328&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on application under section 104, the sub-divisional officer`
  line `is satisfied that any person taking or retaining possession of a plot of land is liable to ejectment, he shall`
  line `order the ejectment of such person and award damages which may extend to four times the annual rental`
  line `value of such plot, calculated in accordance with the sanctioned rates applicable to hereditary tenants.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on the date of the order of ejectment, there is any ungathered crop or other produce belonging`
  line `to the person ordered to be ejected, the applicant shall become owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The sub-divisional officer shall submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed`
  line `by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(4) Any damages awarded under this section shall be recovered as arrears of revenue and paid to the`
  line `person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (37329)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Consequences of failure to file application under section 102 or 104.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37329&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `If no application`
  line `under section 102 or 104 is made within the period of limitation prescribed therefore, and the person`
  line `ejecting the tenant from, or taking or retaining possession of, land, otherwise than in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, cultivates such land, such person shall become--`
  line
  line `(i) if he possesses proprietary interest in such land, khudkasht-holder; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if he does not possess proprietary or tenancy interest in such land, a hereditary tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (37330)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `No separate relief claimable, if not claimed in revenue court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37330&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `A person who has made an`
  line `application under section 102 or 104, shall not be entitled to institute a separate suit or proceeding in a`
  line `civil court for any relief which he might and ought to have claimed and has not claimed.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (37331)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Tenant's right to claim inquiry for illegal exaction and other matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37331&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `If any landholder or`
  line `his agent--`
  line
  line `(i) dishonestly collects a premium prohibited by this Act, or any sum, or produce in excess of the`
  line `amount which is due as arrears of rent, or as sayar, or`
  line
  line `(ii) charges interest on an arrear of rent, not expressly allowed by this Act or at a rate exceeding`
  line `that allowed by this Act, or`
  line
  line `(iii) realises, by proceedings in court or otherwise, any rent of which payment has been remitted,`
  line `or, before the expiry of the period of suspension, any rent of which payment has been suspended`
  line `under the provisions of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(iv) habitually refuses or neglects to deliver to the tenant a receipt, or does not prepare and retain`
  line `a counterfoil of the receipt in the manner prescribed by this Act, or`
  line
  line `(v) without reasonable cause, credits or applies a payment made towards rent otherwise than in`
  line `accordance, with the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `the sub-divisional officer shall, on the application of the tenant, if made within six months of the`
  line `contravention of the provision of this Act to which the complaint relates, institute an inquiry and, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the charge is established, shall award to the tenant monetary compensation not exceeding`
  line `two hundred rupees and submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the`
  line collector.
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (37332)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Power to award compensation in proceedings for arrears of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37332&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the course of`
  line `proceedings for the realisation of arrears of rent, the trial or the confirming court finds that the landholder`
  line `has committed any of the acts enumerated in clauses (i) to (v) of section 108, it may award to the tenant`
  line `compensation, not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) If such compensation is awarded by the trial court, the record of the case shall be submitted for`
  line `confirmation of the order passed by it to the sub-divisional officer, and if by the confirming court, to the`
  line collector.
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (37333)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Prosecution of landholder for illegal exaction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37333&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `If a landholder or his agent collects from a`
  line `tenant any lag or neg, he shall be deemed to have committed an offence of extortion within the meaning`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (Act XLV of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (37334)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Compensation for exaction by landholder and for false complaint by tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37334&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a`
  line `landholder compels his tenant to render any service, or makes use of any cattle or any agricultural`
  line `implement of his tenant against the will of such tenant, whether for remuneration or not, the`
  line `sub-divisional officer shall, on the application of the tenant made within one month of such service or use`
  line `and on the charge being established, award to the tenant a sum, not exceeding one hundred rupees, as`
  line compensation.
  line
  line `(2) If, as a result of inquiry, the sub-divisional officer finds that the complaint is false, and either`
  line `vexatious or frivolous, he shall award to the landholder a sum, not exceeding one hundred rupees, as`
  line compensation.
  line
  line `(3) After deciding the case, the sub-divisional officer shall submit the record for confirmation of the`
  line `order passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (37335)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Penalty for habitual infringement of rights of tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37335&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `If a landlord habitually infringes the`
  line `rights of a tenant under this Act, he shall, notwithstanding anything in section 7 of the Ajmere`
  line `Government Wards Regulation, 1888 (I of 1888), be deemed to be a "landlord who is disqualified to`
  line `manage his own property" within the meaning of section 6 of the said Regulation and his property shall`
  line `be liable to be taken under the superintendence of the Court of Wards.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (37336)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Penalty for illegal entry on a holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37336&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant against whom an order of ejectment from`
  line `a holding or any portion thereof has become final and who re-enters into or remains in occupation of such`
  line `holding or such portion, as the case may be, without the written, consent of the person entitled to admit`
  line `him as tenant, shall be deemed to have committed an offence of criminal trespass within the meaning of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (Act XLV of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) If a landholder enters upon a holding in the possession of a tenant with the object of dispossessing`
  line `him of such holding, otherwise than under the provisions of this Act, such landholder shall be deemed to`
  line `have committed an offence of criminal trespass within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person is convicted of such offence and it appears to the court convicting him that the`
  line `tenant or the landholder has, by reason of anything done in the course of the commission of the offence,`
  line `been dispossessed of any land, the court shall order such tenant or landholder to be reinstated in such`
  line land.
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (37337)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Compensation, how realisable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37337&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `Any compensation awarded under this Chapter shall be`
  line `recovered as arrears of revenue and paid to the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (37338)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Exemption of muafidar.`
  content `The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to a muafidar.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37338&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (37339)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37339&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) A rent-free grant means a grant by a landlord of a right to hold land rentfree with or without consideration.`
  line
  line `(2) A grant of land at a favourable rate of rent means a grant held at a rent which, at the time when`
  line `such grant was made, was below the rent generally payable by a tenant-at-will for land of the same class`
  line `in the neighbourhood.`
  line
  line `(3) A village service grant means a grant made rent-free or at a favourable rate of rent on condition of`
  line `rendering any service to the village community.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (37340)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Grant which cannot be resumed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37340&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) No claim shall be entertained for the resumption of`
  line `a grant--`
  line
  line `(a) in khalsa area, if such grant has been held from a date prior to 1818; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other part of the State, if such grant has been held from a date prior to 1874; or`
  line
  line `(c) which is hereditary and was made out of personal regard for the grantee or in lieu of his past`
  line `services and loyalty to the grantor and big family; or`
  line
  line `(d) which is held unconditionally; or`
  line
  line `(e) which is not resumable under the terms of the grant; or`
  line
  line `(f) to a charitable institution or for the maintenance of a sacred building so long as such institution`
  line `or building exists.`
  line
  line `(2) A holder of a grant to which clause (a), (b), (c), (d) or (e) of sub-section (1) applies and who has`
  line `continuously been in possession thereof for twenty-five years immediately before the commencement of`
  line `this Act, may, on an application made within one year of such commencement and on payment of`
  line `compensation adjudged under sub-section (3), be declared a biswadar of such grant and shall, on such`
  line `declaration, be liable to pay such revenue as may be fixed thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) The compensation to be paid under sub-section (2) shall be four times the annual rental value of`
  line `such grant, calculated at sanctioned rates applicable to hereditary tenants.`
  line
  line `(4) On a declaration being made under sub-section (2), the sub-tenant, if any, of such grant shall`
  line `become a hereditary tenant thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) When land revenue is fixed on a grant in respect of which a declaration is made, the proprietor of`
  line `such grant shall as prescribed be entitled to claim reduction in the revenue payable by him by an amount`
  line `equal to the amount of revenue fixed under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (37341)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Grounds on which certain grants may be resumed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37341&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 117,`
  line `a landlord may apply for the resumption of a grant--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of a grant held for the performance of religious service, on the ground--`
  line
  line `(a) that the object for which the grant was made has ceased to exist; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the grantee has died, leaving no heir entitled to succeed him under the law applicable`
  line `to the deceased; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the grantee has ceased to render the service which he is bound to render;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of a grant for the performance of secular service, on the ground that the landlord no`
  line `longer requires such service or the grantee has ceased to render such service;`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of a village service grant, on the ground that the grantee has ceased to render the`
  line service;
  line
  line `(iv) in case of a grant held for the life-time of the grantee or for a term, on the ground that the`
  line `grantee has died or the term has expired, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(v) in case the grant is held at the pleasure of the grantor, on the ground that it is so held;`
  line
  line `(vi) in case of a grant to which the provisions of clause (f) of section 117 apply, on the ground`
  line `that the institution or the building has ceased to exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (37342)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `How to deal with resumable grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37342&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `If the trial court finds on Inquiry that the grant is`
  line `resumable under section 118, it shall--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case to which the provisions of sub-clause (a) or (b) of clause (i), or clause (ii), (iv), (v)`
  line `or (vi) of section 118 apply, declare the person in possession--`
  line
  line `(a) a hereditary tenant if, on the date of the application for resumption, such person has been`
  line `in continuous occupation of such grant for twelve years or more; or`
  line
  line `(b) as holding without title, if the period of his occupation on such date is less than twelve`
  line `years, and order his ejectment from such grant; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case to which the provisions of sub-clause (c) of clause (i) or clause (iii) of section 118`
  line `apply, order the ejectment of the grantee and appoint a suitable successor in office with or without the`
  line `consent of the landlord, as the court deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (37343)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Application of certain Chapters and sections to grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37343&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) A grantee may--`
  line
  line `(i) obtain a declaration of his status;`
  line
  line `(ii) make improvements and claim compensation therefore;`
  line
  line `(iii) plant trees;`
  line
  line `(iv) claim reinstatement in his holding, if wrongfully dispossessed; and`
  line
  line `(v) eject a person taking or retaining possession of his land in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this Act and claim damages,`
  line
  line `and the respective provisions of the Act relating to such matters shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to him as`
  line `they apply to a hereditary tenant.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of Parts II and III of Chapter VIII and of section 62 and sections 108 to 110 and`
  line `sections 164 to 168 shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to a grantee at a favourable rate of rent as they apply to`
  line `a hereditary tenant.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sections 88, 89 and 111 and of Chapters XIV and XV, so far as they are`
  line `applicable, shall apply to a grantee as they apply to a hereditary tenant.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount of a decree for arrears of rent passed against a grantee at a favourable rate of rent, if`
  line `not satisfied within four months of the date on which such decree becomes final, shall, on an application`
  line `to the tahsildar, be recovered under sections 88 and 89 as if it were a sum due on account of sayar and`
  line `paid to the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (37344)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Grants, how far transferable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37344&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise provided in sub-section (2), no grantee`
  line `shall transfer by sale, mortgage, gift or otherwise his interest in a grant which is liable to resumption`
  line `under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No grantee shall let the whole or any portion of his holding for a term exceeding three years, or`
  line `within three years of any portion of such holding being held by a sub-tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (37345)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Void transactions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37345&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `A transaction by which a grantee transfers or lets his holding or a portion`
  line `thereof in contravention of the provisions of section 121 shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (37346)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Power to hear cases of grantees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37346&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `An application under section 117, 118 or 120, shall be`
  line `entertained, heard and decided by the sub-divisional officer who shall submit the record of the case for`
  line `confirmation of the order or the decree passed by him to the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (37347)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Applicability of Part III.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37347&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `No notification under sub-section (3) of section 1 shall be made in`
  line `respect of Part III of this Chapter, unless, in the area to which such part is applied, rent-rates have been`
  line `determined and the record-of-rights has been framed in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Chief Commissioner is satisfied that in such area the rent-rates determined in the`
  line `year of settlement and the record-of-rights framed in such year and maintained since are reliable, he may`
  line `accept such rent-rates, with or without modification, and such record-of-rights, as framed and determined`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (37348)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power to form and alter Patwaris circles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37348&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `The collector may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Chief Commissioner, divide the area of the State into mahals, thoks or other convenient units, and`
  line `arrange them into girdawars' and patwaris' circles and may alter the number and limits of such circles,`
  line `but no such division, arrangement or alteration shall be final unless it has been sanctioned by the Chief`
  line Commissioner.
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (37349)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Appointment of patwaris.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37349&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `The collector shall appoint a patwari to each circle for preparing`
  line `and maintaining the record-of-rights and registers specified in this Act and for performing such other`
  line `duties as the Chief Commissioner may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (37350)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Appointment of girdawars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37350&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `The collector shall appoint one or more girdawars in each tahsil`
  line `for the proper supervision, maintenance and correction of the annual registers and records, and for such`
  line `other duties as the Chief Commissioner may prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (37351)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Cadre and pay of girdawars and patwaris.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37351&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may fix the cadre,`
  line `grades and pay of girdawars and patwaris and other staff required for the preparation and maintenance of`
  line `the record-of-rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (37352)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Girdawars and patwaris to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37352&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `Every girdawar and patwari shall be deemed`
  line `to be a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (Act XLV of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (37353)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Maintenance of maps and fieldbooks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37353&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `The collector shall maintain a map and a field book of`
  line `each village in the State and shall cause annually, or at such longer intervals as may be prescribed, to be`
  line `recorded therein all changes in the boundaries of each village, mahal or field, and shall correct any error`
  line `in such map or field book.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (37354)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Obligation of owners as to boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37354&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every landlord of a village, mahal or field`
  line `is bound to maintain and keep in repair the permanent boundary marks and the collector may at any time`
  line `order such landlord--`
  line
  line `(a) to erect proper boundary marks on such village, mahal or field; or`
  line
  line `(b) to repair or renew, in such form and with such material as he may order all such boundary`
  line marks.
  line
  line `(2) If such order is not complied with within thirty days from the communication thereof, or such`
  line `longer period as the collector may allow, he shall cause such boundary marks to be erected, repaired or`
  line `renewed, and shall recover the charges incurred from the landlord concerned as arrears of revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) Survey marks shall, as prescribed, be maintained and kept in repair by the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (37355)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title Record-of-rights.
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37355&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a record-of-rights for each village, or if a mahal or other`
  line `unit formed under section 125 consists of two or more villages or portions of villages, the record may be`
  line `prepared for each such village or portion separately.`
  line
  line `(2) The record-of-rights shall include the following documents:--`
  line
  line `(i) a khewat which shall comprise--`
  line
  line `(a) a register of all the proprietors in the village, including the proprietors of specific areas,`
  line `and, in estates mentioned in the Second Schedule, maintenance-holders; and`
  line
  line `(b) a register of jagirdars and muafidars.`
  line
  line `(ii) a khatauni which shall be a register of persons cultivating or occupying land as tenants or`
  line `otherwise; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a wajib-ul-arz which shall be a record of customs obtaining in the State or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section the word "proprietor" shall include a person in possession of`
  line `proprietary rights under a mortgage or lease.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (37356)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Contents of certain registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37356&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `The registers specified in clauses (i) and (ii) or sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 132 shall specify the nature and extent of the interest of each person recorded therein and shall`
  line `be prepared in the prescribed form.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (37357)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Registers of revenue-paying, revenue-assigned and revenue-free villages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37357&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `The collector`
  line `shall prepare and maintain--`
  line
  line `(a) a register of all revenue-paying villages, mahals, thoks or other units, specifying the revenue`
  line `assessed on each and the person by, or through whom it is payable; and`
  line
  line `(b) a register of all revenue-free and revenue-assigned villages and areas, specifying the authority`
  line `and conditions for exemption or assignment as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (37358)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `The annual registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37358&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The collector shall be responsible for maintaining the`
  line `record-of-rights specified in clauses (i) and (ii) of sub-section (2) of section 132, and, for that purpose,`
  line `shall annually, or at such longer intervals as may be prescribed, cause to be prepared an amended set of`
  line `such registers, and the registers so prepared shall be called annual registers.`
  line
  line `(2) The collector shall cause to be recorded in the annual registers all changes that may take place as a`
  line `result of succession or transfer or otherwise, and shall correct any error in such registers.`
  line
  line `(3) No entry in the wajib-ul-arz shall be altered except as a result of inquiry in any settlement or`
  line `record operations in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (37359)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Obligation to furnish information necessary for compilation of certain record-of-rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37359&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person, obtaining possession by succession or transfer of any proprietary or`
  line `other right which is required by this Act or any rule made thereunder to be recorded in any register`
  line `prescribed by clause (i) or clause (ii) of sub-section (2) of section 132, shall report such succession or`
  line `transfer to the prescribed authority. If such person is a minor or otherwise disqualified, the guardian in`
  line `charge of his property shall make such report.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such person, or, if he is a minor or otherwise disqualified, his guardian, shall furnish, on the`
  line `requisition of the patwari, girdawar or any other officer or employee of the revenue department, engaged`
  line `in compiling such register, all information necessary for the correct compilation thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) No revenue court shall entertain any application under this Act by the person so succeeding or`
  line `otherwise obtaining possession, until such person, or, if he is a minor or otherwise disqualified, his`
  line `guardian, has made a report required by this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the word "transfer" shall include a family settlement.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (37360)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Decision of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37360&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `All disputes affecting the entries in the annual registers shall be decided`
  line `in the following manner:--`
  line
  line `(i) those relating to entries to be made in the khewat, on the basis of possession or, if possession is`
  line `doubtful, on the basis of summary inquiry into the question of title;`
  line
  line `(ii) those relating to class or tenure of any tenant, the rent payable by him or any other matter to`
  line `be recorded in the khatauni, in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the terms of the lease, if`
  line `any, so far as they are consistent with such provisions; and`
  line
  line `(iii) those relating to boundaries, on the basis of the survey map, and in case one was not prepared`
  line `or is not available, on the basis of actual possession.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (37361)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Inquiry into cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37361&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Contested cases relating to entries in the annual registers and to`
  line `boundary disputes shall be heard and decided by the sub-divisional officer who shall submit the record of`
  line `the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(2) Uncontested cases shall be disposed of by the tahsildar.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (37362)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Certain decisions, no bar to civil suit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37362&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `No entry made or order passed under section 138,`
  line `relating to entries in the khewat, or to boundary disputes, shall debar any person from establishing his`
  line `right to any property in a court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (37363)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Value of entries and decisions in contested cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37363&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 139,`
  line `the decision given under sub-section (1) of section 138 shall be binding on the parties to the dispute and`
  line `an entry made in the khewat or khatauni under the order of the sub-divisional officer or the collector in a`
  line `contested case shall be presumed to be correct until the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (37364)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Appointment and punishment of lambardars and patels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37364&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `The collector may appoint one or`
  line `more lambardars or patels in a village, mahal or thok and may suspend, remove or dismiss them.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (37365)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Record and rent-rate operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37365&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `official Gazette, order that in any estate mentioned in the Second Schedule or group of such estates or in`
  line `any other area of the State, a preparation or revision of the record-of-rights or survey or re-survey, or the`
  line `determination of rent-rates for any class or classes of soils, or some or all of these operations be taken in`
  line `hand, whether by revision of the most recent records and rent-rates or otherwise, and may appoint an`
  line `officer as a record officer or rent-rate officer to be in charge of record or rent-rate operations, as the case`
  line `may be, and as many assistant record officers as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date of the notification every such estate or group of estates or other area shall be held to`
  line `be under record, or rent-rate operations or both, as the case may be, until the issue of another notification,`
  line `declaring such operations to be closed therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (37366)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Powers of the record officer, assistant record officer and rent-rate officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37366&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) For such`
  line `period and to such extent as he deems fit, the Chief Commissioner may empower the record officer or the`
  line `rent-rate officer--`
  line
  line `(i) to perform the duties and exercise the powers of a collector under Part I of this Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to commute, abate, enhance and determine rents in accordance with the provisions of Part III`
  line `of this Chapter in any area to which such Part has been applied.`
  line
  line `(2) An assistant record officer shall exercise such powers of the record officer or any other revenue`
  line `court as the Chief Commissioner may, by order in writing, specify, and shall submit the record of cases`
  line `decided by him to the record officer for confirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (37367)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Sanctioned rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37367&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `The sanctioned rates shall be the rates determined under this Part:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in any part of the State such rates have not been determined, a revenue court requiring`
  line `the use of such rates, otherwise than for deciding abatement, enhancement or commutation of rent cases,`
  line `shall in the manner prescribed work out appropriate rates after making local inspection and considering`
  line `the rent generally payable by tenants of the same class for land of the same class in the vicinity, and the`
  line `rates so worked out shall be deemed to be the sanctioned rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (37368)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Duration of rent-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37368&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `When rent-rates are determined for any area, they shall not, unless the`
  line `Central Government otherwise directs, be determined again until a period of not less than twenty years`
  line `has elapsed.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (37369)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Circle and soil classification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37369&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, any estate or group of estates or any other area for which`
  line `rent-rates in money are to be determined, has not been divided into assessment circles, or, if classification`
  line `of the soil thereof has not been made, or if the Central Government orders a revision of the existing`
  line `circles or soil classification or both, the rent-rate officer shall make circles and classify she soils, and shall`
  line `propose rent-rates for each class of soil in each circle.`
  line
  line `(2) If such estate, group of estates or area has previously been divided into assessment circles, the`
  line `rent-rate officer shall propose separate rates for each circle, and for each separate class of soil previously`
  line `demarcated therein, unless, by order of the Central Government, the circles or the classification of soils,`
  line `or both are revised by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (37370)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Basis of rates for hereditary tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37370&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rates proposed by the rent-rate officer for`
  line `hereditary tenants shall be based on genuine and stable rents paid by such tenants.`
  line
  line `(2) In proposing rates in accordance with sub-section (1), the rent-rate officer shall have regard to the`
  line `provisions of sections 63 and 64 and shall, before framing his proposals, take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the value of the produce with a view to seeing that the valuation of the holdings of hereditary`
  line `tenants at the proposed rates does not exceed one-fifth of such value;`
  line
  line `(b) the prices of agricultural produce prevailing in the main markets of the neighbourhood;`
  line
  line `(c) the changes in the crops grown and in the amount of the produce;`
  line
  line `(d) the rotation of crops and periods of rest which tenants usually allow to land;`
  line
  line `(e) the average size of holdings in the circle and methods of cultivation;`
  line
  line `(f) the results of crop-cutting experiments in the local area for which rates are proposed and in the`
  line `different parts of the State generally;`
  line
  line `(g) the level of bighori rates, if payable in any particular area in respect of certain crops; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as generally affect rents payable by tenants.`
  line
  line `(3) In proposing rates for occupancy and exproprietary tenants, the rent-rate officer shall have regard`
  line `to the scale of rents prescribed for such tenants in relation to the scale of rent payable by hereditary`
  line `tenants under sections 63 and 64.`
  line
  line `(4) The rent-rate officer shall also record for each village whether the rates proposed by him are`
  line `applicable without modification to the village as a whole or to a specified area or class of soil therein, and`
  line `in case they require modification, the extent of such modification; and, in their application to such village,`
  line `area or class, the rates shall be deemed to be modified accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (37371)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Provision for rates in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37371&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `The rent-rate officer shall propose rates for the`
  line `commutation of--`
  line
  line `(a) rent paid by batai, or partly by batai and partly by bighori, into fixed money rent; and`
  line
  line `(b) rent paid by batai into bighori at current rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (37372)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Procedure in publishing and sanctioning rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37372&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rent-rate officer shall publish, in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed, the proposals and records made by him under sections 147 and 148`
  line `and shall receive and consider any objection which may be made to him.`
  line
  line `(2) When such objections, if any, have been considered and disposed of, the rent-rate officer shall`
  line `submit the proposals and records made by him after such modification, if any, as he may deem fit, to the`
  line `Chief Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the proposals, the Chief Commissioner may direct further inquiry into any of the`
  line `matters contained therein and shall, if satisfied that such proposals have been rightly framed, submit them`
  line `to the Central Government for acceptance.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall either sanction the proposed circles, soil classification, rates and`
  line `other matters recorded under sections 147 and 148, or may, for reasons to be recorded, sanction them with`
  line `such modification as it deems fit, and the rates so sanctioned shall be sanctioned rates.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (37373)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Civil suit relating to record-of-rights and certain other matters barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37373&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 139, no suit shall be brought in any civil court in respect of any matter concerning`
  line `the entries in, or preparation of, a record-of-rights, the framing, publication, signing or attestation of such`
  line `record or of any part of it, or the determination of rent-rates under the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (37374)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Commutation of rent from kind to cash.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37374&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an occupancy, an exproprietary or a`
  line `hereditary tenant has heretofore paid his rent by bighori or batai, or partly by bighori and partly by batai,`
  line `he may apply for the commutation of such rent to a fixed money rent:`
  line
  line `Provided that in an area where rents are paid by bighori for some crops and by batai for others, the`
  line `tenant may elect to have that portion of the rent which is payable by batai alone commuted into bighori`
  line `on the basis of sanctioned rates appropriate to him, and in such case the court shall commute that portion`
  line `which is payable by batai by fixing a rate of rent per bigha for batai crops grown on the holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (37375)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Commutation of rent from cash to kind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37375&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `Where the rent of an occupancy, an exproprietary`
  line `or a hereditary tenant has been commuted under section 151, he may, subject to the provisions of`
  line `clause (ii) of section 161, apply that the rent of such holding be declared as payable by batai in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sections 63 and 64, or, if before commutation it was payable partly by`
  line `bighori and partly by batai, in the manner it was payable before such commutation, and the court shall`
  line `make such declaration.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (37376)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Grounds of abatement of fixed money rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37376&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `The fixed money rent or the bighori, determined`
  line `under section 151, of an occupancy, an exproprietary of a hereditary tenant shall be liable to abatement on`
  line `one or more of the following grounds:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the rent payable by the tenant is substantially greater than the rent calculated at the`
  line `sanctioned rates appropriate to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the productive power of the land held by the tenant has decreased by any cause beyond`
  line `the control of the tenant during the currency of the present rent; or`
  line
  line `(c) in case of fixed money rent, that the area of his holding has been decreased by diluvion, or by`
  line `the taking up of land for a public purpose, or for a work of public utility.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (37377)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Ground of enhancement of fixed money rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37377&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The fixed money rent of the bighori,`
  line `determined under section 151, of an occupancy, an exproprietary or a hereditary tenant, shall be liable to`
  line `enhancement on one or more of the following grounds:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the rent payable by the tenant is substantially less than the rent calculated at the`
  line `sanctioned rates appropriate to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the productive power of the land held by the tenant has increased by an improvement`
  line `effected by, or at the expense of, the land holder, other than a work in respect of which irrigation dues`
  line `are payable under section 87 or which is carried out under the scheme sanctioned by the`
  line `Central Government under section 5 of the Delhi and Ajmer-Merwars Land Development`
  line `Act, 1948 (LXVI of 1948); or`
  line
  line `(c) in case of fixed money rent, that the area of the holding has been increased by alluvion.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (37378)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Order for determination, commutation or variation of rent, when to take effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37378&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Except as`
  line `otherwise provided in sub-section (3) of section 163, every order for abatement, enhancement,`
  line `commutation or determination of rent shall take effect from the commencement of the agricultural year,`
  line `next following the date of such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (37379)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Joinder of parties in cases relating to variation of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37379&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) An application for commutation,`
  line `abatement or enhancement of rent may be made against, or by, any number of tenants collectively:`
  line
  line `Provided that all such tenants are tenants of the same landholder, and all the holdings in respect of`
  line `which the application is made are situated in the same village.`
  line
  line `(2) No order shall be passed in any such proceeding affecting the interest of any person, unless the`
  line `court is satisfied that he has had an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) The order shall specify the extent to which each of the holdings is affected thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (37380)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Determination of rent on partial ejectment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37380&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `When a tenant is ejected under an order of a`
  line `court from a part only of his holding which is assessed to fixed money rent, or being entitled to surrender`
  line `a part of such holding legally surrenders such part, either he or his landholder may apply for the`
  line `determinations of the rent of the remainder.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (37381)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Rent, how calculated for commutation, variation or determination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37381&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of sections 160 and 163, when rent is to be determined or commuted into fixed money rent, or`
  line `the fixed money rent or the bighori determined under section 151 is to be abated or enhanced, the court`
  line `shall calculate the rent--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of hereditary tenants, in accordance with the rates sanctioned for hereditary`
  line `tenants; and`
  line
  line `(b) in case of occupancy and exproprietary tenants, in accordance with rates which shall conform`
  line `to the scale prescribed for such tenants in relation to hereditary tenants under the provisions of`
  line `sections 63 and 64:`
  line
  line `Provided that, for special reasons to be recorded, the court may modify the sanctioned rates applicable`
  line `to any particular case, and it shall modify such rates if it finds that, as a result of their application, the rent`
  line `arrived at on commutation, abatement, enhancement or determination, as the case may be, is substantially`
  line `different from the money value of the rent payable by the same class of tenants under the provisions of`
  line `sections 63 and 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (37382)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Meaning of "substantial" in certain sections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37382&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 153, 154 and 158`
  line `a difference of ten per cent. or more shall be deemed to be substantial.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (37383)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Basis of variation of rent in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37383&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceedings for abatement of fixed`
  line `money rent on the ground that the area of the holding has decreased by diluvion or by the taking up of`
  line `land for a public purpose or for a work of public utility, or under the provisions of section 37, or for`
  line `enhancement on the ground that the area of the holding has increased by alluvion, the court shall abate or`
  line `enhance the rent with reference to the existing rent and the decrease or increase in the area of the holding.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceedings for enhancement of fixed money rent or the bighori determined under`
  line `section 151 on the ground that the productive power of the holding has increased by an improvement`
  line `effected by, or at the expense of, the landholder or for abatement of rent on the ground that such power`
  line `has decreased by any cause beyond the control of the tenant, the court shall enhance or abate the rent with`
  line `reference to the existing rent and the increase or decrease of the productive power.`
  line
  line `(3) In an application for the determination of the fixed money rent of a portion of a holding under`
  line `section 157, the court shall determine the rent with reference to the rent payable before ejectment or`
  line `surrender and the loss of area due to such ejectment or surrender.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (37384)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Period for which rent is not liable to modification.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37384&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in section 163, when`
  line `the rent of an occupancy, an exproprietary or a hereditary tenant has been commuted, abated or enhanced`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act, it shall not be liable to be commuted, abated or enhanced`
  line unless--
  line
  line `(i) in case of abatement or enhancement of rent--`
  line
  line `(a) the revenue payable by the landlord has been revised; or`
  line
  line `(b) there has occurred a decrease or increase in the productive power or the area of the land`
  line `held by the tenant, as provided in clauses (b) and (c) of sections 153 and 154; or`
  line
  line `(c) the sanctioned rates have been altered; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of commutation of rent, a period of three years, or such longer period as may have`
  line `been extended under section 83, has elapsed since the date of the last commutation order.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (37385)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Applications for variation of rent, by whom to be entertained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37385&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in`
  line `sub-sections (2) and (3), all applications for commutation, abatement, enhancement or determination of`
  line `rent shall be made to, and heard and decided by, the sub-divisional officer who shall submit the record of`
  line `the case for confirmation of the order passed by him to the collector.`
  line
  line `(2) When any area is under rent-rate operations, or when rent-rates have been determined under this`
  line `Act for any area, or accepted under the proviso to section 124 and such area is placed under record`
  line `operations, all such applications relating to such area shall be filed in the court of the rent-rate officer or`
  line `the record officer, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) If such application is heard and decided by the rent-rate officer or the record officer, the record of`
  line `the case shall be submitted for the confirmation of the order passed by him to the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (37386)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Provision of rent and revenue in an emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37386&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in this Act or`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force, when the Central Government is satisfied that an emergency`
  line `has arisen in any area, it may appoint to such area an officer of the grade of an assistant commissioner and`
  line `invest him with all or any of the following powers:--`
  line
  line `(a) the powers of a rent-rate officer and a record officer;`
  line
  line `(b) if sanctioned rates have not been determined or have not been accepted under the proviso to`
  line `section 124 for such area, powers to commute, abate, enhance or determine rents summarily`
  line `otherwise than in accordance with such rates; and`
  line
  line `(c) powers to revise revenue assessed on any estate, mahal, village or thok in which rents have`
  line `been commuted, abated, enhanced or determined under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) If, as a result of any order passed by the officer appointed under sub-section (1), the assets of any`
  line `estate or area are increased or decreased, such officer shall increase or decrease, as the case may be, the`
  line `revenue of such estate, village, mahal or thok in the proportion which such increased or decreased assets`
  line `bear to the assets before such increase or decrease.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order passed by such officer in exercise of the powers conferred on him under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be submitted for confirmation to the collector or such other officer as the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, by order, specify and shall take effect from such date as the officer passing it or the`
  line `confirming court may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (37387)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Remission or suspension of rent in agricultural calamities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37387&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the occurrence of an`
  line `agricultural calamity, affecting the crops of any village or area, the Central Government or any authority`
  line `empowered by it in this behalf, may remit or suspend for any period the whole or any portion of the rent`
  line `payable by a tenant in respect of any holding affected by such calamity.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Central Government or such authority remits or suspends rent, it shall remit or suspend`
  line `for a like period the whole or portion of tie revenue assessed on such village or area.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (37388)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Bar to collection of rent remitted or suspended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37388&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `No landholder shall collect, under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or otherwise, any rent the payment of which has been remitted or, during the period`
  line `of suspension, any rent the payment of which has been suspended under section 164.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (37389)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Period of suspension to be excluded in computing period of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37389&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `When the payment`
  line `of rent has been suspended in accordance with the provisions of section 164, the period during which the`
  line `suspension continues shall be excluded in computing the period of limitation under this Act for the`
  line `recovery of such rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (37390)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Remission for calamity by court decreeing claim for arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37390&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it Appears to a court`
  line `passing a decree for arrears of rent that the area of the holding was so decreased by diluvion or otherwise,`
  line `or that the produce thereof was so diminished by drought, hail, pests, deposit of sand or other like`
  line `calamity during the period for which the arrears are claimed, or that the full amount of rent payable by the`
  line `tenant for that period cannot be equitably decreed, it may, with the sanction of the collector, allow such`
  line `remission from the rent payable by the tenant for that period as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The court allowing such remission shall submit the record of the case for confirmation of the order`
  line `passed by it to the collector.`
  line
  line `(3) No remission made under this section shall be deemed to vary the rent payable by the tenant`
  line `otherwise than for the period in respect of which such remission was made.`
  line
  line `(4) When remission of rent is granted in accordance with the provisions of this section, the collector`
  line `shall, on the application of the landlord, grant a remission of revenue in proportion to the rent remitted for`
  line `the corresponding area belonging to the same landlord.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (37391)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Jurisdiction of certain courts excluded in cases of remission and suspension of rent or revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37391&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in this Act, an order for revision, remission or suspension of rent or`
  line `revenue passed under this Chapter shall not be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (37392)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Cases cognizable by revenue courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37392&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `A case which is cognizable by a revenue court under`
  line `this Act shall be heard and decided by such court, and no court other than a revenue court shall, except as`
  line `provided in this Act, hear or decide any such case, or any suit or application based on a cause of action in`
  line `respect of which relief could be obtained in a revenue court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--If the cause of action is one in respect of which relief might be granted by the revenue`
  line `court, it is immaterial that the relief asked for from the civil court is different from, greater than, or`
  line `additional to, that which the revenue court could have granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (37393)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Procedure of revenue courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37393&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may frame rules for regulating the`
  line `procedure of revenue courts and may, in doing so, extend or apply any provisions of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (V of 1908), with or without modification:`
  line
  line `Provided that until such rules are framed and, subject to them when framed, the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), shall, except when they are inconsistent with anything in`
  line `this Act, or relate to special suits or proceedings outside the scope of this Act, apply, in so far as they are`
  line `applicable, to proceedings under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (37394)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Application of Indian Limitation Act, 1908.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37394&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `Sections 4, 5 and 12, sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14 and sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 17 of the Indian Limitation Act, 1908, shall apply,`
  line `mutatis mutandis, to applications and other proceedings under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (37395)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Limitation in cases under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37395&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `Except as provided in section 171, no application under`
  line `this Act shall, if the period for filing it is specified therein, be filed after the expiry of such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (37396)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Payment of court-fees under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37396&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court-fee shall be payable when the first`
  line `application is filed by a party to any proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any second or subsequent application made in the course of the same proceeding shall bear a`
  line `court-fee stamp of four annas only:`
  line
  line `Provided that when, under this Act, any sum is collected by a revenue court as arrears of revenue or`
  line `as sayar on behalf of an applicant or a party to a proceeding, or when the amount of a decree is paid into`
  line `court under section 98, such court shall, notwithstanding anything in this Act, before making payment to`
  line `the person entitled, deduct seven and a half per cent. of the amount so collected or paid into court as`
  line `court-fee and pay the balance to such person:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if in any case, after issues have been framed and any evidence has been`
  line `recorded, the first application is dismissed or withdrawn, the trial court or the confirming court, as the`
  line `case may be, shall assess the amount of the court-fee which, but for the provisions of sub-sections (1)`
  line `and (2), the applicant would have been liable to pay under the Court-Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), as`
  line `applied to the State, deduct the amount, if any, paid as court-fee under sub-section (2) and recover the`
  line `balance as arrears of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (37397)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Subordination of courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37397&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) All revenue courts in the State shall be subordinate to the Chief`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(2) All revenue courts specified in sub-clauses (iv) to (viii) of clause (35) of section 4 shall be`
  line `subordinate to the collector, and the revenue courts specified in sub-clauses (vi) to (viii) of the said clause`
  line `shall be subordinate to the sub-divisional officer of the area within which they exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) An assistant record officer shall be subordinate to the record officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (37398)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Place of sitting of revenue courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37398&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue court mentioned in sub-clause (i), (ii) or (iii)`
  line `of clause (35) of section 4 and, subject to the orders of the collector, a revenue court mentioned in`
  line `sub-clause (v) of the said clause may hear and dispose of cases at any place within the State.`
  line
  line `(2) A sub-divisional officer may hold his court at any place within his sub-division or, with the`
  line `sanction of the collector, in any other part of the State.`
  line
  line `(3) A tahsildar or a naib-tahsildar may hold his court at any place within his tahsil.`
  line
  line `(4) A revenue court, mentioned in clause (a) or (b) of section 180, may sit in any part of the State`
  line `specified by the collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (37399)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Chief Commissioner's power to confer powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37399&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, confer on an assistant commissioner or a sub-divisional officer all or`
  line `any of the powers of a collector under this Act to be exercised in respect of such cases or class of cases or`
  line `such other matters as may be specified in such notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (37400)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Collector's power to place assistant commissioner in charge of subdivision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37400&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `collector may place any assistant commissioner in charge of a sub-division and may remove him`
  line therefrom.
  line
  line `(2) The assistant commissioner so placed in charge shall be sailed a sub-divisional officer and shall,`
  line `subject to the control of the collector, exercise all the powers conferred, and discharge all the duties`
  line `imposed, upon the sub-divisional officer by this Act, or any rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (37401)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Collector's powers to authorise certain courts to entertain and dispose of applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37401&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `The collector may, by order in writing, empower--`
  line
  line `(a) an assistant commissioner to entertain and decide applications, and to receive and dispose of`
  line `cases submitted for confirmation of a decree or an order passed by a tahsildar, which a sub-divisional`
  line `officer is empowered under this Act to entertain, decide, receive or dispose of; and`
  line
  line `(b) a naib-tahsildar of not less than three years standing, to entertain and dispose of such`
  line `applications as a tahsildar is empowered under this Act to entertain and dispose of.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (37402)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Powers of revenue courts to refer cases for investigation and report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37402&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `Any revenue court`
  line `may refer any case which it is empowered to dispose of to any revenue court subordinate to it for`
  line `investigation and report.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (37403)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Powers of Chief Commissioner to create shamlat committee and courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37403&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Commissioner may--`
  line
  line `(a) create an honorary court and invest it with powers to hear and dispose of cases which a`
  line `tahsildar may hear and dispose of under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) establish a punchayat in any village or group of villages of the State, and invest such`
  line `punchayat with powers to hear and dispose of cases which a tahsildar may hear and dispose of under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, and to perform such other duties as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) sanction the creation of a shamlat committee in any village or town which has at least three`
  line `hundred acres of stable land as shamlat deh; and`
  line
  line `(d) define the jurisdiction of the courts created or established under clause (a) or (b) of this`
  line `section and provide for submission of the cases decided by them for confirmation to courts specified`
  line `by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no court so created or established under clause (a) or (b) shall hear or decide a case if`
  line `such court or a member thereof is interested in the result of such case:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if, at the commencement of this Act, there exists a shamlat committee in any`
  line `village or town to which the provisions of clause (c) apply, the Chief Commissioner may recognise such`
  line `committee as one created under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (37404)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Decree or order to be final in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37404&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sections 185, 186 and 187, a decree or an order which is not required by this Act to be submitted to a`
  line `confirming court shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (37405)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Submission to confirming court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37405&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `When, under the provisions of this Act, a revenue court is`
  line `required to submit the record of a case to a confirming court, it shall not comply with such provisions--`
  line
  line `(i) unless any of the parties to such case has, within seven days of the decree or the order passed`
  line `therein, made an application bearing a court-fee stamp of the value of two rupees and eight annas to`
  line `such revenue court, requesting that the record be submitted for confirmation; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such decree or order is passed on the admission of a party to the case, or in terms of a`
  line `compromise; or is based on the award of an arbitrator appointed by the parties; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if the parties to the case apply in writing that they accept the decree or order as final:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any party challenges a decree or an order mentioned in clause (ii) on the ground that`
  line `it does not conform to the compromise or the award, or that it goes beyond it, such court shall, on the`
  line `application of such party, submit the record to the confirming court.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (37406)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Form of decree or order to be submitted for confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37406&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order submitted for`
  line `confirmation shall contain a concise statement of the case, the points for determination, the decision`
  line `thereon, and the reasons for such decision.`
  line
  line `(2) A decree submitted for confirmation shall conform to the order passed and shall be prepared only`
  line `in cases and in the form prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (37407)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Procedure for confirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37407&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `When the record of a case is received by a confirming court and`
  line `the provisions of the section under which such, record is submitted do not specify the manner of`
  line `confirmation, such court shall--`
  line
  line `(i) call upon each of the parties to file, if he wishes to do so, a written statement setting forth,`
  line `concisely and under distinct heads, the grounds of objection to the decree or order, numbered`
  line `consecutively without any argument or narrative;`
  line
  line `(ii) treat the written statement of the party against whom the decision was given by the trial court`
  line `as memorandum of appeal, and that presented by the other party as memorandum of cross-objection;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iii) after hearing the parties or such of them as appear before him, pass an order which a court of`
  line `appeal may pass under the provisions of Order 41 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that no such written statement shall be entertained on behalf of a party who has not applied`
  line `for submission of the record under clause (i) of section 182, unless it bears a court-fee stamp of the value`
  line `of rupees two and annas eight.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (37408)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Review by the Chief Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37408&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may, on his own motion, or on`
  line `the application of a party, review any decree or order passed by him and may rescind, vary or confirm it.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (37409)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Review by other courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37409&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `Every other revenue court may review its judgment, order or decree`
  line `to correct clerical or arithmetical errors, or errors arising therein from any accidental slip or omission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for review shall be entertained--`
  line
  line `(a) after the record has been submitted to a confirming court; or`
  line
  line `(b) if such application cannot be disposed of without recording further evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (37410)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37410&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner or, in respect of a decree or an order passed by a civil`
  line `court, the Judicial Commissioner may, on the application of a party, call for the record of any case which`
  line `is decided by a court subordinate to him and if such subordinate court appears--`
  line
  line `(a) to have exercised a jurisdiction not vested in it by law, or`
  line
  line `(b) to have failed to exercise a jurisdiction so vested, or`
  line
  line `(c) to have acted in the exercise of its jurisdiction illegally or with material irregularity, he may`
  line `make such order as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for revision shall be made within three months of the passing of an order or a`
  line `decree sought to be revised.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (37411)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Power to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37411&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `The collector may, on the application of a party, transfer an`
  line `application pending before a subordinate revenue court or a case submitted to such court for confirmation`
  line `of a decree or an order from such court to any other court of competent jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the collector refuses to transfer such application or case, he shall submit the record`
  line `for confirmation of the order passed by him to the chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (37412)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Power of collector to transfer and withdraw cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37412&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `The collector may--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer any case submitted to him or to any subordinate court for confirmation of a decree or`
  line `an order to any subordinate court of competent jurisdiction; or`
  line
  line `(b) by order recall to his own court any case pending for confirmation in a subordinate court; or`
  line
  line `(c) withdraw from any court subordinate to him any case other than a case which is submitted to`
  line `such court for confirmation, and try such case himself or transfer it to any other subordinate court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the collector himself hears and decides any case withdrawn under clause (c) he shall`
  line `submit the record for confirmation of the order passed by him in such case to the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (37413)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Sub-divisional officer's power to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37413&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `A sub-divisional officer may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the collector, transfer any case or class of cases pending before him to any assistant`
  line `commissioner competent to try such case or class of cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (37414)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Power of record officer to transfer and withdraw cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37414&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `A record officer may transfer any`
  line `case or class of cases pending before him to any assistant record officer, and may withdraw any case or`
  line `class of cases from an assistant record officer and try such case or class of cases himself or transfer the`
  line `same to any other assistant record officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the record officer himself tries any case so withdrawn, he shall submit the record for`
  line `confirmation of the order passed by him in such case to the Chief Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (37415)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Transfer of cases by the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37415&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `A district judge may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Judicial Commissioner, transfer any case submitted to him for confirmation of an order or a decree to`
  line `an additional district judge or to a subordinate judge, and such additional district judge or subordinate`
  line `judge shall dispose of such case as if he had the powers of a district judge under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (37416)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `Dispute as regards ownership of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37416&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in connection with any action taken by a`
  line `landlord under clause (iii) of section 9, a dispute arises between him and any other person who claims to`
  line `have a proprietary interest in the land in respect of which such action is taken, either party may apply to`
  line `the collector for the decision of such dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) On the receipt of such application, the collector shall follow the procedure specified in section 38`
  line `and the provisions of that section shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the case.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in consequence of the order passed by the collector, any loss results to a tenant or to any other`
  line `person having an interest in the land to which such order relates, the collector shall, before submitting the`
  line `record of the case to the confirming court, award monetary compensation to such tenant or other person.`
  line
  line `(4) Any compensation awarded under this section shall be recovered as arrears of revenue and paid to`
  line `the person entitled.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (37417)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Procedure when plea of proprietary right raised in revenue court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37417&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise`
  line `provided in sections 38 and 193, if in any proceeding, other than a proceeding under section 137, a`
  line `question of proprietary right is raised and such question has net previously been determined by a court of`
  line `competent jurisdiction, the revenue court shall frame an issue on the question of proprietary right, and`
  line `submit the record to, the competent civil court for the decision of that issue only.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--A plea of proprietary right which is clearly untenable and intended to oust the`
  line `jurisdiction of the revenue court shall not be deemed to raise a question of proprietary right within the`
  line `meaning of this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--A question of proprietary right does not include the question whether land is`
  line `khudkasht or niji jot.`
  line
  line `(2) The civil court, after refraining the issue, if necessary, shall decide such issue and return the`
  line `record together with its finding thereon to the revenue court which submitted it.`
  line
  line `(3) The revenue court shall then proceed to decide the case, accepting such finding and shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything in this Act, submit the record to the district judge for confirmation of the order`
  line `or the decree passed by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (37418)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Procedure when plea of tenancy raised in civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37418&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) If in any suit relating to`
  line `agricultural land instituted in a civil court, any question regarding tenancy right arises and such question`
  line `has not been previously determined by a court of competent jurisdiction, the civil court shall frame an`
  line `issue on the plea of tenancy and submit the record to the sub-divisional officer for decision of that issue`
  line only.
  line
  line `Explanation.--A plea of tenancy which is clearly untenable and intended only to oust the jurisdiction`
  line `of the civil court shall not be deemed to raise a plea of tenancy.`
  line
  line `(2) The sub-divisional officer, after refraining the issue, if necessary, shall decide such issue and`
  line `return the record together with his finding thereon to the civil court which submitted it.`
  line
  line `(3) The civil court shall then proceed to decide the suit, accepting the finding of the revenue court on`
  line `the issue referred to it.`
  line
  line `(4) The finding of the revenue court on such issue shall, for the purposes of appeal, be deemed to be`
  line `part of the finding of the civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (37419)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Reference to Judicial Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37419&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where either a civil or a revenue court is in doubt`
  line `whether it is competent to try any case, the court may refer such case with a statement of the reasons`
  line `therefor to the Judicial Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the court is a revenue court subordinate to the collector, no reference shall be made`
  line `except with the previous sanction of the collector.`
  line
  line `(2) On any such reference being made, the Judicial Commissioner may order the court either to`
  line `proceed with the case or transfer such case to such other court as may be declared by him to be competent`
  line `to try it.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (37420)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `Provision for injunction and appointment of receiver.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37420&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, in the course of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act, it is proved by affidavit or otherwise--`
  line
  line `(a) that any property, tree or crop standing on the land to which such proceeding relates is in`
  line `danger of being wasted, damaged or alienated by any party to such proceeding, or`
  line
  line `(b) that any party to such proceeding threatens, or intends, to remove or dispose of the said`
  line `property, tree or crop to defeat the ends of justice,`
  line
  line `the revenue court before which any such proceeding is pending may grant a temporary injunction and, if`
  line `necessary, appoint a receiver.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person against whom an injunction has been granted under sub-section (1) may offer to give`
  line `cash security of an amount determined by the court to compensate the other party in case the matter in`
  line `dispute is decided against such person, and the court may withdraw the injunction on his depositing such`
  line security.
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (37421)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Cases in which legal practitioners may appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37421&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `A legal practitioner shall be entitled to`
  line `appear in any proceeding on behalf of a party before a revenue court under the provisions of this Act in`
  line `the following cases only and in no others--`
  line
  line `(i) to file a written statement, and to argue a case, before a confirming court,`
  line
  line `(ii) to prosecute and defend cases under Chapters IX and X and Part III of Chapter XII, and`
  line
  line `(iii) to file an application for revision under section 187 and to argue the case before the court`
  line `hearing such application.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (37422)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Persons who may appear before a revenue court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37422&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `A party to a proceeding or his authorised`
  line `agent may appear, plead or act before a revenue court.`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (37423)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 200
  title `Costs in revenue courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37423&sectionno=200&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `A revenue court may allow and apportion the costs of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act in any manner it thinks fit, but if it orders that costs shall not follow the event,`
  line `it shall record its reasons for the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (37424)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 201
  title `Power of revenue court to summon persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37424&sectionno=201&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue court may summon any person`
  line `whose attendance it considers necessary for the purpose of disposing of any proceeding before it.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless exempted from personal appearance in court under sub-section (1) of section 133 of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), a person so summoned shall appear at the time and place`
  line `mentioned in the summons in person or, if the summons so allows, by his authorised agent.`
  line
  line `(3) The person attending in obedience to the summons shall be bound to state the truth upon any`
  line `matter respecting which he is examined or makes a statement, and to produce such document and other`
  line `thing relating to any matter which may be within his power or possession as the court may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (37425)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 202
  title `Mode of service of summons or notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37425&sectionno=202&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `(1) A summons issued by a court acting under this`
  line `Act shall, if practicable, be served (a) personally on the person to whom it is addressed, or failing him`
  line `on (b) his authorised agent or (c) an adult male member of his family who is residing with him.`
  line
  line `(2) If service cannot be so made, or if any person mentioned in sub-section (1) refuses to accept`
  line `service, the summons may be served by posting a copy thereof at the usual or last known place of`
  line `residence of the person to whom it is addressed, or, if that person does not reside in the tahsil in which`
  line `such court is held, and the case to which the summons relates has reference to land in that tahsil, then by`
  line `posting a copy of the summons on some conspicuous place in or near the estate wherein the land is`
  line situated.
  line
  line `(3) If the summons relates to a case in which persons having the same interest are so numerous that`
  line `personal service on all of them is not reasonably practicable, it may, if the court so directs, be served by`
  line `delivery of a copy thereof to such of those persons as the court nominates in this behalf and by`
  line `proclamation or publication in a local paper of the contents thereof for the information of the other`
  line `persons interested in such case.`
  line
  line `(4) A summons may, if the court so directs, be served on the person named therein, either in addition`
  line `to, or in substitution for, any other mode of service, by forwarding the summons by post in a letter`
  line `addressed to such person under a certificate of posting.`
  line
  line `(5) When a summons is served in accordance with the provisions of this section, it shall be deemed to`
  line `have been duly served.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of this section "summons" shall include a "notice" which a court may issue`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (37426)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 203
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 63 of 1950, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-12-1950).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37426&sectionno=203&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may make rules for the purpose of giving`
  line `effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for demarcation of pasture land and niji jot;`
  line
  line `(b) for the attestation of leases and agreements;`
  line
  line `(c) for the collection and disbursement of cesses, or assessment and recovery of irrigation dues,`
  line
  line `and for decision of disputes in respect of them;`
  line
  line `(d) for the training of patwaris and girdawars;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the appointment and transfer of girdawars and patwaris, and other staff required`
  line `for the maintenance of the record-of-rights, their salaries, qualifications, duties, leave, removal,`
  line `dismissal or any other punishment;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribing the form, contents, method of preparation, attestation and maintenance of the`
  line `record-of-rights, annual registers, maps, field-books, and other records to be kept under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) for the erection of boundary and survey marks, and for their repairs and renewals, and for the`
  line `recovery of costs in respect of such erection, repairs or renewals;`
  line
  line `(h) for providing the principles on which the part of the holding from which a tenant is to be`
  line `ejected be determined and for the demarcation of such part;`
  line
  line `(i) for recording transfers and changes affecting interest in land, whether proprietary or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(j) regulating the imposition of fines for failure to notify succession or transfer;`
  line
  line `(k) for the appointment of lambardars and patels, the duties to be performed by them, the`
  line `remuneration, if any, to be paid to them and for their removal and dismissal;`
  line
  line `(l) for appeals or other modes of obtaining redress in cases of punishments inflicted on girdawars,`
  line `patwaris, and other employees of land records establishment, and on lambardars and patels;`
  line
  line `(m) for the guidance of officers in cases for the determination, enhancement, abatement and`
  line `commutation of rent;`
  line
  line `(n) for the guidance of record officers and rent-rate officers;`
  line
  line `(o) for the remission and suspension of rent and revenue in agricultural calamities;`
  line
  line `(p) defining the powers of various classes of officers and revenue courts to hear and dispose of`
  line cases;
  line
  line `(q) for the establishment of honorary courts and village punchayats and for regulating their`
  line `work; and`
  line
  line `(r) for collection of fines, compensation, damages or other sums imposed, awarded or ordered to`
  line `be paid under the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^1[(s) for the levy of a fee in respect of any application or the grant of any relief under this Act in`
  line `cases not specifically provided for.]`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule the Chief Commissioner may provide that any contravention of such rule shall`
  line `be punishable with a fine not exceeding fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette and shall also be laid`
  line `before Parliament, as soon as may be, after such publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (37427)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 204
  title `Reinstatement of tenant ejected before commencement of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "three months" (w.e.f. 1-12-1950).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37427&sectionno=204&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, between the first`
  line `day of June, 1942 and the commencement of this Act, the landlord of an estate mentioned in the Second`
  line `Schedule had ejected a tenant from his holding, otherwise than in accordance with the Ajmere Land and`
  line `Revenue Regulation, 1877 (2 of 1877), such tenant may, within ^1[nine months] of such commencement,`
  line `apply to the tahsildar to be reinstated in such holding.`
  line
  line `(2) An application under this section shall state--`
  line
  line `(i) the Khasra number and area or other description of such holding and the name and address of`
  line `the person who is in possession thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) if such holding is held by a tenant, the khasra, number and area of other land in the possession`
  line `of the landlord which may be given to the applicant in lieu of the holding from which he was so`
  line `ejected; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The tahsildar shall, after hearing the parties and making such other inquiry as he deems fit,`
  line order--
  line
  line `(i) if such holding is in the possession of the landlord, that the applicant be reinstated in such`
  line `holding; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if such holding is held by a tenant, that an area of the land mentioned in clause (ii) of`
  line `sub-section (2) or any other land in the possession of the landlord which is approximately equal in`
  line `value to the holding from which the applicant was so ejected be allotted to him and demarcated on the`
  line spot.
  line
  line `(4) If the applicant cannot be reinstated in his holding under clause (i), or allotted other land under`
  line `clause (ii) of sub-section (3), the tahsildar shall award to the applicant monetary compensation which`
  line `shall be six times the annual rental value of the holding from which he was so ejected calculated at`
  line `sanctioned rates applicable to hereditary tenants, recover the amount of such compensation as arrears of`
  line `revenue and pay it to him.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall be reinstated in his holding under this section unless, within such time as may be`
  line `allowed by the tahsildar, he pays to the landlord compensation, calculated in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, for any improvement on such holding made by such landlord.`
  line
  line `(6) The applicant shall be a hereditary tenant of the land in which he is reinstated or which is allotted`
  line `to him under this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The tahsildar shall, after deciding the case, submit the record for confirmation of the order passed`
  line `by him to the sub-divisional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (37428)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 205
  title `Provision for pending and other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028&sectionId=37428&sectionno=205&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_000010_195042_1517807326028
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act, no court`
  line `shall entertain any proceeding for the establishment or enforcement of a claim, prohibited by, or`
  line `inconsistent with, the provisions of this Act, whether such claim arose before or after such`
  line commencement.
  line
  line `(2) A proceeding, in respect of any matter covered by this Act, pending in any civil or revenue court`
  line `at the commencement of this Act shall, notwithstanding anything contained in section 169, be heard and`
  line `decided by such court in accordance with the corresponding provisions of this Act, and if there is no such`
  line `corresponding provision, it shall be quashed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the record of every case in which the proceeding`
  line `is so quashed shall be submitted for confirmation in accordance with the provisions of section 183 by the`
  line `court quashing the proceeding to the court to which it is immediately subordinate and the court to which`
  line `the record is so submitted shall follow the procedure specified in section 184.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
